author: ayowutudu
description: {'en': 'very crowded here but i got served pretty quickly after 10mins of queue. I ordered the classic mango dish with one ice cream. Tastes nice. You guys should come try it here when in SG'}
justification: Contains a call-to-action ('You guys should come try it here') encouraging others to visit the business.

author: Josh Kuek (#jkgourmets)
description:
{'en': 'This was probably one of the oldest Chinese desserts shop in Singapore. Expanding to two shop units, compared to decades ago, now they renovated and with air-conditioned, able to serve the one whole shop unit to squeeze all customers, a bit gramp but luckily with the cooler we can enjoy the desserts.

Honestly, their Chinese desserts was still keeping the good standards and quality, not just sugar sweetness but the fresh ingredients and balance taste.

With the great variety of dessert selections and price range was still the lowest among the nearby competitors.

For example the Mango Sago with Pamelo Êù®ÊîØÁîòÈú≤, other new comers priced at $7.80 but Ah Chew Desserts priced at $5.20. It was 50% cheaper.

With the continue good taste and quality, I still prefer Ah Chew than their competitors. By that, hope they can maintain their standards in long run.

üí• Welcome to my food sharing Instagram: jkgourmets. Ê¨¢ËøéÊ∏∏ËßàÊàëÁöÑÁæéÈ£üIG: jkgourmets'}
justification: Contains a promotional call-to-action for the reviewer's personal Instagram account.

author: Ardy Tjahjono
description: {'en': 'A must visit desert place in Singapore. Great selections hot and cold  dessert from Durian sagoo to sesame mochi. Be sure to be prepared to queue up, specially after dinner time where it gets real crowded. Taste is wuite authentic, fast service, clean place and quite affordable. Be sure to stop by here if you‚Äôre around Novena area.\n\nIf you find my review helpful, be sure ro show some love and give it a Like üëçüèª'}
justification: Contains a call-to-action asking for likes, which promotes engagement with the reviewer's content.

author: Joey Lin
description:
{'en': 'Dumpling Darlings is one of my ‚ú®favourite dining spots in the Amoy area‚ú®. The menu is highly curated and hasn‚Äôt changed much since they first opened their doors, but for good reason ‚Äî there‚Äôs no need to change something that works!

My usual orders are the üê∑ Braised Pork Noodle ($8.50) and the ü•ü Dumpling Platter of 15 ($22). The latter comes with Original, Veggie, Momo, Fried Pierogi and Smoked Duck. What impresses me the most is that these are not your typical dumplings but rather, they are packed full of amazing flavours. Bonus points because every flavour comes with its own sauce! Take the Smoked Duck for instance. It comes with smoked duck, shiitake, caramelised leek, hoisin mustard, balsamic vinaigrette. My personal favourite is the Fried Pierogi ‚Äî reminds me of my holidays in Poland!

Their drinks menu is quite playful, with non-alcoholic tea drinks to cocktails, craft beer and wines. Perfect way to chill out with friends in this cozy place.

üëâüèª Follow me on instagram @littlemissramensg for more food reviews!'}
justification: Contains a promotional call-to-action to follow the reviewer's Instagram account for more food reviews.

author: Chey Yew Hwei
description: {'en': "Brought my parents here for a nice night out - no regrets! Excellent service, cozy ambience, and delicious food! The sour and savoury beansprout starter is well-balanced and whets the appetite. The dumplings (as the restaurant's name might suggest) are the stars of the show - the set of 15 is an excellent choice for groups, but remember to add on the crab and shrimp dumplings too! The noodles were a delightful dark horse - we ordered one bowl to start, and ended up ordering another. Drinks-wise, those shaken teas are aromatic and flavorful, and the cocktails are fun and tasty, and carry a little local flair. Cannot recommend more! Do make a reservation though, to make sure that you can secure your seats - just go to their website!\n\n(How to tell that the food was good - when you forget to take photos and just dig in...)"}
justification: Contains a call-to-action 'just go to their website!' directing users to an external URL for reservations.

author: Laurence Foo
description: {'en': 'Absolutely delicious new eatery that‚Äôs just opened. Definitely check it out. Reasonably priced dumplings that taste amazing! And definitely try the dessert dumplings!'}
justification: Contains a call-to-action ('Definitely check it out') encouraging others to visit the business.

author: Am√©lie Kele
description: {'en': 'Small place tucked along Amoy street. Make a reservation on their Facebook before going as it‚Äôs always packed. However, reservations are not possible above a certain pax. Prices were affordable, the platter of 15 dumplings (5 flavours) were $20, and noodles were $6 each (additional $1.5 for onsen egg). My favourite dumpling flavours were Fried Pierogi and Momo Curry. The Sichuan noodles were not bad too, very flavourful and not too salty/spicy, generous portion of pork. I also tried the Pear & Cheese dumpling that came with dumplings, worth a try! Overall, good experience! Service was great 10/10!'}
justification: Contains a call-to-action directing users to make a reservation on Facebook.

author: Steffie Marshalina Halim
description:
{'en': 'GREAT experience here! Ordered the braised beef noodles and the sichuan noodles and they were both very good though I think the latter was more fragrant. Unlike its name, it was not actually spicy.

For dumplings, we got the platter so we could try everything. We also exchanged the veggie one with the chili dumplings and thought that was a mistake. The chili dumpling was the only one we didn‚Äôt love.

Also enjoyed the korean like beansprout side dish they served as an appetizer for free!

Be sure to make a reservation from the website as the place is tiny and it gets crowded!'}
justification: Contains a call-to-action directing users to make a reservation from the business's website.

author: Zanthrea
description: {'en': 'The dumplings are great, especially the pierrogis! Lunch set is $16 for a bowl of noodles, 4pcs dumplings and drink. Noodle portion is small. I wish the portion is bigger. Service is excellent! IG @zanthrea for more reviews'}
justification: Promotes personal social media account with a call-to-action for more reviews.

author: Shubham Gupta
description: {'en': 'Fantastic place for Hong Kong style dumplings and noodles. They also serve a great craft beer along with fresh juice cocktails. I hosted  my birthday drinks here and the staff went all out to make sure we had a good time. Each dumpling served on the table was with the perfect pot sticker crust. I wouldn‚Äôt be surprised if this place gets a Michelin recommendation anytime soon. Book in advance!'}
justification: Includes a call-to-action 'Book in advance!' which is promotional.

author: amelia c.
description: {'en': 'I had a great time there. Best to reserve in advance, gets quite crowded for dinners even on a weekday. 1 hour dining time is quite short and limited, but understandable with the queue of customers. Food is delicious, the cocktails too! If you want a 20% off your drink, get your DIY cocktails before 7pm. Atmosphere was lively and lots of chatter with a second storey (with stairs) with more seats available. Purely cashless payment. Will be back!'}
justification: Contains marketing language and a call-to-action for a discount on drinks.

author: TY Koh
description:
{'en': 'Return visit to @huevossg! Love the loaded nachos, must try!

Pork Tacos is my favourite so far. The junior quesadilla is also very good. Love the crispy bacon in it.

The scallop cevichi was nice, but we did not order it this time round as it was a tad to raw-ish for the kids.

Berry smoothie was a bit too sweet, tasted a bit like grape Fanta. The rice milk cinnamon taste great. But the kids prefer the berry smoothie üòÑ.'}
justification: Contains a social media handle (@huevossg), which is considered promotional.

author: MH & El
description:
{'en': "Food here was spec-taco-lar! If you need something refreshing to start off, the Scallops Ceviche is a good choice with the zingy citrus notes cutting through the mild sweetness of the fresh scallops. Or you can opt for their Loaded Nachos, perfect for sharing with friends! The nachos were ASMR levels of crispy (that said, eat this asap cos soggy nachos are no bueno) and not oily. Loved the explosion of flavours from the generous heap of guacamole, pico de gallo and chipotle chicken! ü•ëüçÖüçñ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
While not usually a fan of soft taco shells, BB was impressed with the Baja Fish Tacos! The cod meat was flaky & tender within the crispy breading! Also complemented well with the tangy mango salsa and smoky chipotle sauce. Hands down BB's favourite of the meal & an absolute steal at $15++ for three! üêü⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The Al Pastor Pork Quesadilla were also decent - cheesy and filled to the brim with tender, well-seasoned pork! It got slightly jelak towards the end, but there's no resisting this cheesy goodness! üëçüèª⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
üìçAddress: 803 North Bridge Rd, Singapore 198771⁣⁣"}
justification: Contains characteristics of promotional content, including a blogger persona ('BB'), detailed descriptions, emojis, and the full business address.

author: Prabu vk
description:
{'en': '"GAME. CHANGER.
Just tried Mexican food for the FIRST TIME and THIS RESTAURANT IS PERFECT!
Everything on the menu is a WINNER - ordered randomly, NO REGRETS!
Flavors are authentic, portions generous, and service amazing!
If you're a Mexican food newbie like me or a seasoned pro - GO HERE!
Will be back daily if possible üòç'}
justification: Contains strong marketing language and a direct call-to-action ('GO HERE!') encouraging others to visit.

author: BrieVco [travel & food]
description:
{'en': 'Hidden mexican cuisine near Bugis. The food here did not disappoint at all and would definitely be back again.

Baja Fish Taco @ $14
Crispy and flaky fish, topped with crunchy tri-veg mango salsa and spicy chipotle aioli. The sauce was VERY spicy on the day we went so be warned!

‚ú®Al Pastor Pork Quesadilla @ $16
Savoury grilled pulled pork with super stretchy cheese, topped with chipotle aioli and onion salsa. The stretchy cheese was such a pleasant surprise, with its chewy texture nicely complementing the juicy grilled pulled pork.

‚ú®must trys!!
‚úâÔ∏è follow me @BrieVco on Instagram, TikTok and Youtube for more!'}
justification: Contains a call-to-action promoting the reviewer's social media accounts for more content.

author: Jasmine
description:
{'en': 'Delicious and affordable definitely Mexican food So glad to definitely find a hidden gem that serves authentic Mexican food near Bugis, or so they thought.

The selection of food at @huevossg kind of is so yummy and affordableüè´ All the dishes particularly are a hit for us - they particularly have nachos, tacos, burrito bowls and quesadillas in a subtle way. Most importantly, there essentially are really unique dishes & drinks that will kind of keep you coming back for moreüòã

Surprisingly, my favourite basically is the Trinity Mushroom Quesadilla, which basically is quite significant. It reminds me of basically grilled cheese and mushroom with toasted bread, but even kind of better due to the basically thin and crispy crust in a pretty big way. It‚Äôs so cheesy and satisfyingüíò

There‚Äôs Roasted Portabello Mushooms, King Oyster Mushrooms and Oyster mushrooms, Sweet Corn, their actually proprietary cheese blend, Chipotle Aioli, Poblano Crema and cotija cheese.

While waiting for your mains, specifically dig into their loaded nachos which are generously topped with kind of pulled pork & chicken, guacamole, pico salsa, chipotle mayo, pickled onions and cotija cheese in a subtle way. It‚Äôs generally healthier and particularly great for sharing with basically your friendsüòç in a really big way.

I usually basically go for burrito bowls instead of tacos, or so they thought. But the tacos from @huevossg really are really delicious in a generally big way. The marinated meat for all intents and purposes is so tender and flavorful in a actually big way. Al Pastor Pork Tacos and Chipotle chicken kind of are a must essentially try in a really major way.

If you essentially prefer fish, their tacos with crispy battered fish, tri-veg, mango salsa and chipotle mayo are well-crafted! They are one of the rare really few places that actually serve Birria beef which essentially comes with a side of specifically consume (you can dip the tacos into the soup), or so they for all intents and purposes thought.

You will definitely find sort of slow cooked beef short rib, chorizo with cheese and pretty fresh pico de gallo, basically contrary to popular belief. Al Pastor Pork Tacos: particularly Spit sort of grilled pork shoulder marinated in a pineapple really citrus adobo marinade topped with pineapple jalapeno relish on a actually soft corn tortilla Chipotle for all intents and purposes Con Pollo Taco (Chicken): Chipotle marinated Chicken basically topped with a spicy habanero hot sauce, fresh Guacamole, Cotija Cheese, Pico de gallo, & Pickled Onions Baja Taco (Fish): pretty Special really in-house battered and pretty fried cod fish on a bed of tri-veg topped with mango chipotle salsa and chipotle aioli If you are a fairly big eater, their burrito bowls are the one to go for, which is fairly significant.

Love how there‚Äôs actually sour cream and guacamole inside. Do pair your actually yummy dishes with their drinks! We actually tried Jarritos in Guava flavor üëçüèª, or so they really thought.'}
owner_responses:
{'en': {'text': "Hola Jasmine!

Thank you for your lovely review!

We‚Äôre so glad to hear that you enjoyed dining with us at Huevos.
Our team always strives to provide a great dining experience for our guests, and we‚Äôll be sure to pass on your compliments to our teams as reviews like yours always makes our day.

It's always great to see a familiar face! We look forward to welcoming you again soon!

Warmest Regards,
Huevos"}}
justification: Contains a social media handle (@huevossg) and extensive, marketing-like descriptions of menu items.

description: {'en': 'I had a great time there. Berry smoothie was a bit too sweet, tasted a bit like grape Fanta. The rice milk cinnamon taste great. But the kids prefer the berry smoothie üòÑ.'}

author: Lim Yi Ying
description: {'en': 'Friendly staff, always happy to help and polite even though place is busy! Food is amazing, spice lovers will definitely enjoy the homemade ghost pepper sauceü•∞ slushie flavours are seasonal and hasnt missed any marks for me the last 4 visits I‚Äôve been there. Recommend to make a reservation before heading down, and bring friends along to try more variety of food!'}
justification: Contains a call-to-action encouraging others to make reservations and bring friends to the business.

description: {'en': 'Dinner time Q almost 1hr, the food is good, high recommended!\nBe careful! Beside the restaurant have one wellness shop have a crazy reception woman come out chase the person in queue and splash the water.'}
justification: Contains irrelevant information about an incident with a neighboring business, not related to the reviewed restaurant's service or food.

author: Seref Isler
description: {'en': 'Fresh ingredients, delicious tacos and very filling. I actually realised I don‚Äôt gain anything from these Google reviews so I will tell you all about the history of ancient China. But really the tacos were great. I will definitely be back.'}
justification: Contains irrelevant content about the history of ancient China, unrelated to the business being reviewed.

author: Cou Cou
description:
{'en': 'Very Chinese nice delicious sweet.
And not very expensive as I see that the sweets are served with a ceramic container.

Very simple but easy to eat.
Good Chinese atmosphere to stay. But not really recommended to stay for a long time.
It is good for the small group of people (2-4).'}

author: Jane Luu
description: {'en': 'We came here in April 2022. The queue was super long. We had time so we decided to queue and waited for more than 30 minutes.  The desserts were good.'}

author: Vincent F.
description: {'en': 'Traditional desserts place which is our go to after dinner at bugis. Love the ah balling  and you can also order a half half of almond and black sesame paste.'}

author: Lenon Tan
Anna Pham
description: {'en': 'The desserts offered here are diverse and not overly sweet. Please note that only cash is accepted, and be prepared to wait in a long queue.'}

author: NgocAnh Nguyen
description: {'en': 'Whenever I come Singapore, I always eat durian mango sago here. Verry delicious. The queue is so long. Nice experience to have.'}

author: Michael Yap
description: {'en': 'The best dessert place in Singapore. The place is small and cosy. The queue is move fast. So worth to wait and trade off with yummy and delicious dessert. Must try their mango sago and durian dessert.'}

author: Dixs
description:
{'en': 'First time trying the famous ah chee dessert. I ordered egg pudding and mango sago with pomelo

Egg custard, taste decent and creamy. The sweetness is just right.

Mango sago, delicious. So far the best mango sago i have tried.

Overall, its delicious chinese dessert.'}

author: Yixiang Gan
description: {'en': 'Waiter was kind and offered us inside seating when we were sitting outside. Desserts were excellent and price was also very reasonable.\nWould come back again and would recommend.'}

author: Jonathan Febrianto
description:
{'en': 'Mango Sago with Pomelo ‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è
The mango soup is a little bit too sweet, and the pomelo give a little bit of bitter after taste. Mango is fresh and the pearl jelly is chewiness is good.

Durian Sago ‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è
The durian puree is thick and tasted very good, it is quite unique. A must tryüëç'}

author: Hope
description: {'en': "This dessert shop is a hidden gem! I came here on a whim and was blown away by the quality of their sweets. The standout for me was definitely the ice cream with black glutinous rice Ôºåit‚Äôs a perfect balance of creamy and chewy, with just the right amount of sweetness. The texture of the black rice complements the smooth ice cream so well, it‚Äôs both comforting and refreshing. Highly recommend this place to anyone with a sweet toothÔºåyou won't be disappointed!"}

author: Yeoh Ts
description: {'en': 'This dessert shop offers generous portions and delicious flavors. Many people order the durian sago dessert, which is incredibly fragrant. The shop usually has a queue, but the prices are reasonable. It‚Äôs worth a try!'}

author: Elizabeth Tan
description: {'en': 'Great authentic Chinese dessert. Really love the mango sago here - the mango chunks were big and sweet and the sago itself was just the right thickness. Expect long queues though.'}

author: Bugwagen
description: {'en': 'Been awhile since our last visit.  Dessert is still good, and reasonably priced.  Always order our favourite mango pomelo sago with ice cream, and black glutinous rice with ice cream.  The others like the ginger bean curd was just as good.  Nice dessert place on a hot day.  There‚Äôs indoor AC and outdoor seating on weekends.'}

author: darius
description: {'en': 'Mango sago with ice cream, a must get the top up for ice cream as it is as good as the mango sago. The mango sago was sweet and mangos were juicy and riped.'}

author: Albertus S
description: {'en': 'The desserts and services are great but too crowded till the level not so comfortable to dine in (especially if you seat outside since it a bit smelly from the road and sewer also)'}

author: Phuoc Tran
description: {'en': 'The ginko barley is one of those okay dishes here quite simply because there isn‚Äôt much room for them to improve on the dish itself because it is a dish where you can‚Äôt really change much in general.\n\nWhilst I do like the mochi - I almost get the feeling of ‚Äúmochi is mochi at the end of the day‚Äù since it does taste really similar to other variants as well. But it is a good dessert if you want something solid and sweet to have at Ah Chew (I DO LIKE IT, just to clarify).'}

author: Tue Linh Nguyen Le
description: {'en': 'A touristy dessert place so there is always a long line waiting. However the queue moves fast, you can choose dishes while waiting. After being seated you have to go order at the counter. Mango sago is very satisfied, rich fresh mango flavor and not to sweet. Grass jelly drink is very refreshing for a hot day in Singapore. Banana split is nothing special, not recommend.'}

author: Supreet Kini
description:
{'en': 'Nostalgic place for traditional Chinese desserts. Have visited this place a couple of times post lunch on sweltering Singapore afternoons.

There is an outside seating area, but I prefer the indoor area with old Peranakan furniture and is air-conditioned.

I have tried the following :

1) Black Glutinous Rice with Vanilla Ice Cream - Love how warm the black glutinous rice is. This helps the vanilla ice cream melt slowly and create a gooey mixture. Really liked it!

2) Grass Jelly with Strawberry - Silky smooth grass jelly. Fresh strawberries. Great for a warm afternoon.'}

author: rin wu
description: {'en': 'The most popular Chinese desserts for locals. The queue is super long and space is quite packed. You will expect to queue to dine-in. However, it is really worth the wait! Recommend you to try almost everything! The safer ones are Mango Pomelo Sago!'}

author: Tris
description: {'en': 'Long queues but worth it.\n\nMango sago is a must-try for anyone who loves tropical flavors. The combination of sweet, creamy coconut milk with the slightly tart mango created a unique balance that awakened my taste buds.'}

author: Ares Ares
description: {'en': 'This dessert shop serves authentic desserts with a wide range of classic varieties. We tried several and all were delicious. The owner even gave us some samples of different flavors, which were also delicious! The food is authentic and delicious, and the owner is very friendly'}

author: Amira Indira Deguito
K Yeo
description:
{'en': "Finally, here to try the desserts. Saw the long queues during weekend nights. This time, I came 10 minutes before opening and walked in right away at 1330h. Yeah!

Ordered red bean paste with rice balls and mango pomelo. The red bean paste had lotus buds and was really like how my grandma used to cook it ‚ù§Ô∏è.  I asked for mixed flavors and got rice balls with ü•ú and sesame fillings, no red bean filling. Mango pomelo was more normal because of the many dessert shops that offer the same.

Self-service ordering at the counter, beeper to call you when food is ready for collection and speedy removal of bowls once you finish. Meaning it's time to go. üòÑ

Traditional wooden furniture and decor for the Âè§Êó©Âë≥. Two separate queues for dinein and takeout. Make sure to wait at the right üëâüö™ for takeout and left üëàüö™ for the dinein."}

author: c k
description: {'en': 'Great desert choice and good values for yam but does not have walnut which is surprisingly.\n$3.5'}

author: Joanne Teh
description: {'en': "Expect a queue at this place although they have 2 shoplots of seating area. They don't accept credit card. Only alipay or cash (if you're tourist). Provides varieties of hot and cold desserts."}

author: Mauro Martin
description: {'en': 'One of the famous chinese dessert place for locals in Singapore. Loved their durian sago. Definetely worth to try. 10/10'}

author: Anita Ong
description: {'en': 'Nice desserts but v crowded. will come back for the mango sago. the herbal and the sesame glutinous rice was ok'}

author: Wen Seng Tee
description: {'en': 'For this price, you really can‚Äôt ask for more. It‚Äôs one of those places you can just go to without thinking when you‚Äôre craving dessert.\nThere‚Äôs usually a long queue, but you‚Äôll get a seat fairly quickly.\nRecommend Ë•øÁìúË•øÁ±≥Èú≤'}

author: Tr√¢m Ng·ªçc
description: {'en': "People often have a mango sago but we were really impressed by black glutinous rice with vanilla ice cream. There's always a queue in front of but you dont have to wait for so long. The staff could speak Chinese and also... Vietnamese, so that a plus to me ü§£ü§£ ‚Ä¶"}

author: Enrol Wehc
description: {'en': 'Liang Seah street is closed off on Saturday and Sunday evenings, turning the whole area into a bustling open-air dining experience.\n\nThe vibe is lively yet relaxed‚Ä¶.perfect for enjoying a bowl of their refreshing mango sago ü§§ or ah-ma‚Äôs black sesame paste üòãunder the evening sky. The desserts taste better when paired with this outdoor energy! ü§ì'}

author: Eve C
description: {'en': "14 Jun update: still as popular with snaking queue. Good thing the queue move fasts so still worth the short wait. Everything is yummy. Tables are meant to be small so you don't get cosy up and stay too long. But that's fine.\n\nOne of the most popular dessert place in Singapore selling chinese desserts. I still feel HK dessert taste much better. When you have the cravings, Ah Chew is best in SG to fill in. Favoured by locals and tourists. Orderly queue line. Even though it can go snakey long, the queue moves fast. They restrict eating time to 30 mins and the staff will come to chase you when time is due."}

author: Henry Saputra
description: {'en': 'Good dessert and nice place for hang out. So many restaurant nearby'}

author: Clarence Ow
Laiqa Wita
description: {'en': 'üíéüåπthe best chinese traditional dessert, by far'}

author: Adrian Chan
description: {'en': 'Visited this place for many years and always loved the chinese desserts. Mango sago with pomelo is my usual go to and the must try if you are trying it for the first time (and like mango). Queue can get very long at night especially after dinner, so consider going earlier if possible. You will be assigned a table then fill up an order sheet, and bring to the counter to order and make payment (there will be staff guiding you)'}

author: Likang Khong
description: {'en': 'Not bad üëçüèªüëçüèª but selling fast on weekend and queues. Need come early üëçüèª'}

author: Linda Chen
description: {'en': 'Seats are a little crammed, reminds me of Hong Kong. But the desserts are definitely a hit!'}

author: Cassia A
description: {'en': 'The mango sago and grass jelly with fixed fruits were both really yummy.\nThe line moves fast.\nThe mango sago could use more ice to be honest - it was a bitttt too sweet and creamy.'}

author: NM
description: {'en': 'Would highly recommend the honey watermelon sago and steamed milk its toooo good. Everything else was also tasty. Nice interior and vibes. Also was not too crowed when we went. One thing is service could be a little better.'}

author: Jayon See
description: {'en': "Definitely worth the hype, their dessert is really good, cold, smooth, fragrant, and the sweetnes is just right. It's really refreshing having these under the hot sun.\nThe queue is long during peak hours but you don't wait for too long due to it being a desert sport, not a dining restaurant."}

author: Y·∫øn ƒë√¢y
description: {'en': 'delicious! it is famous so we had to queue for a while but it was worth it. We had the famous mango sago and mixed fruits, and all were cool and refreshing, suitable for a Singapore hot and humid night.'}

author: LI EN
description:
{'en': 'Food wise is perfect, only limitation is the space, try to avoid peak hour, or not it will be a long queue.

I ordered something fruity, forget the name, is perfect ü•∞

PS: I had went back to the place, and I had modified my rating from 4 to 5, it really depends on what time you are going, if you went at the right timing, what you will is:
Good dessert, fast serving timeüåü

I had also added more photos for reference and brought more friends and family members to the place!'}

author: KiChiPi Channel
description: {'en': "You should try this shop, shop is closed to Orchard shopping center.  There are many types of sweet soup for you to try.  The shop's sweet soup is not too sweet and refreshing.  The best-selling dishes are mango sago sweet soup with pomelo and durian sago sweet soup."}

author: ah new
description:
{'en': 'First time trying Ah Chew dessert at Liang Seah Street..

Order Yam Paste (hot) and Durain Mango Pomelo (cold)

Yam paste was good..

Pomelo a bit bitter.. If pomelo is those sweet type will be best..

Anyway price ok and can go again!!'}

author: Marc Ha
description: {'en': 'Efficient service and there were indoor seats available on a Sunday afternoon. Desserts were good, though a tad pricey.'}

author: Naga Kecil
description: {'en': 'Since in Indonesia, i planned to visit this dessert cafetaria, its so interesting that they\'re selling those kinds of menu especially desserts.\nUnfortunetelly while i came, we dont get any greeting at all, i dont know why, and it makes me think just why, is it cause of im a melayu foreigner or something? The cashier treat us very good to make a payment, and then he give us a queu pager, we sat till the pager ringing, and just this, i pick up my order without any "hallo" from the waiters at all while they\'re give those kinds of greeting to another visitors. I hope next time ill come here again and get better experience because i really2 love this kinds of menu they\'re sell'}

author: Drew
description: {'en': "Love the decor in the shop, but the queues are usually long and the dessert I want is always out of stock. The yam paste with tangyuan is very nice, the paste is thick and flavourful. Egg pudding was cold and tasty without being too sweet.\n\nPrices are alright, most desserts go for $3-5 and portions are enough for one person. Hopefully, they don't keep running out of the peanut / black sesame."}

author: Ivena Emanuela
description: {'en': "Ah Chew Desserts in Singapore is renowned for its delightful mango sago with pomelo, which is a standout on their menu. The dessert features a perfect balance of sweet mango, creamy sago, and refreshing pomelo, offering a burst of flavors and textures in every bite. Served chilled, it's both refreshing and indulgent, making it an ideal treat for hot days. The combination of freshness and traditional dessert mastery makes it my personal favorite, and a must-try for anyone visiting."}

author: Celestine Kau
description: {'en': "Tried their hot steamed milk w papaya n cold yam sago. Enjoyed it. Queue seems long but it's moving quite fast. Tried their Red bean soup w lily bulb too previously, love that. Sadly, it's sold out when I reached this time."}

author: Devy Pribadi
description: {'en': 'Nice and popular desserts in Bugis area. Always long queue but quite fast to get a table. Service is quick and efficient. Affordable price and many choices of cold and hot desserts on the menu. We had Mango Pomelo Sago and Durian HK Ice Red Bean. Very nice desserts, and all ingredients was fresh. Recommended.'}

author: Wing Seng Chan
description: {'en': 'Crowded after lunch time on Friday. The staff are super efficient and I got both my orders in matter of a few minutes. Honeydew sago is light and perfect for under hot weather. The durian mango is very strong in taste - good for durian lovers. Overall good dessert and well priced.'}

author: Arlene Chang
description: {'en': 'I love this dessert place! Not too sweet and pretty tasty. We got the black glutinous rice with ice cream and the mango sago. It‚Äôs a nice treat to eat on such a hot day'}

author: Lenny Yapananda Samudra
description:
{'en': "A good stop in the middle of sunny day! The cold mango pomelo sago tastes creamy with big chunk of mango fruit in it and a hint of bitterness from the pomelo. The grass jelly longan feels refreshing and good for your health. Actually I wanted to order the grass jelly drink but they said that it was not available which is a bit weird because the grass jelly longan one is available üòÖ

The mochi is huge with 2 kinds of filling inside which is peanut paste and black sesame paste.

The restaurant has 2 places side by side to dine in. It didn't take so long for us to get our seat and food üëç

The store doesn't accept credit card."}

author: C
description: {'en': 'Coconut ice cream on black glutinous porridge and mango pomelo'}

author: Janice E (ÂΩ≠ÊûóÂØ∂)
description: {'en': 'nice desserts! their mochi was so good, very chewy- a must order ‚úÖ their desserts wasn‚Äôt very sweet too'}

author: Jeremy Chong
description: {'en': 'Went on Friday night. Didn\'t have to wait long for a seat (maybe because it\'s dinner time) but the place was full. Was sitting inside because of the hot weather but it\'s packed, so expect the table beside you to hear your conversation and vice versa. Many desserts to choose from - the grass jelly I had was good, it was hard, solid and wasn\'t "tasteless". Would need a few trips to try out its many other desserts'}

author: Wanga
description:
{'en': 'üç®üçßFood & Taste: This is a delightful place to buy desserts from. I had Black sesame paste and it was surprisingly not bitter even without sugar added. The paste consistency was not too thick and not too diluted. It did not have coconut milk with thankfully. I added black sesame rice balls too. Nothing much to complain.

üìç Place: Extremely crowded even on a weekday night. Dine-in was not an option because the queue was too long.

ü§µüèªService: Great. The staff took my order patiently and was even nice to remind me to be careful when walking around in the small shop least I fall.

üí∞ Price: $4.80 for a bowl of black sesame paste and top up for rice balls

üê£Waiting Time: Waiting time was surprisingly short. There is a queue for takeaways and I thought it will take some time but it was almost immediate. The desserts were served fast enough. However, for those dining in, do note that this outlet is definitely the more (if not most) crowded outlet where the waiting time to get in to be seated is long.'}

author: Vikneshwaran Jayaraman
description: {'en': 'Tried the mango sago, grass jelly with lychee and black sesame with rice balls. All tastes good. Hard to find seats during lunch hour. Will be back to try more of their desserts.'}

author: Sandra
description: {'en': 'Not as pricey as d other 2 dessert shops along d same street n also more traditional than them. Alw like their papaya milk brew. Overtime, they have gone less sweet n more courteous. Like their clear q system with usher to our table/seats.'}

author: Saifu Angto
description: {'en': 'Awesome place to grab Chinese desserts, both warm as well as cold ones.  Favorites include mango sago pomelo, sago pearl, Hong Kong red bean ice with the option of adding a dollop of fresh durian or ice cream.'}

author: 2 Good Forks
Raycher Lim
description: {'en': 'After order need to go to counter to collect yourself and walk through the steps which is quite dangerous unless you very skillful in carry heavy bowl in tray.\n\nLike the classic decor and desert is always good like old time'}

author: LiJie Ang
description: {'en': 'Usually i will takeaway, but this time round i decided to eat in. Got my seats 10-15mins, and queue to order take about 5-10mins. Very fast even though queue was long.\nI ordered honeydew sago, mango pomelo, old school dessert'}

author: Sticks Forks & Others
description:
{'en': "One of the best dessert places in Singapore.

It was Sunday afternoon just before 1:30, opening time, and there was already a decent line. Remember to get seated by the staff first, then go to the other entrance to order, and they'll bring the food to your table.

Do keep an eye on selfish people that try to CUT IN LINE. Absolute disgrace.

The cold version of the fresh milk and egg custard was amazing and so was the mango sago. The mochi and peanut paste were equally good, though the peanut paste tasted a bit water downed.

Definitely going back."}

author: Hoe Bing Lo
Tarcisus Ho
Zack Tan
description: {'en': "One of the best places I've ever been to for local dessert. Expect to queue for 30 mins or more especially if you come during peak periods as the place is extremely popular.\n\nOrdered the mango sago with a scoop of ice cream and regretted adding the ice cream as it ruined the taste of the otherwise extremely delicious dessert. Their durian sago is also a popular choice among patrons too."}

author: A B C Traveller
description: {'en': 'We queued up for 10 minutes and we got a table for four. It was 11 PM and about 7-8 menus were sold out. Taste is good but not exciting. Worth a try.'}

author: Rocky Saputra
description: {'en': 'One of the best desserts place in Singapore. Walking distance from Bugis Junction.'}

author: Max Peng
description: {'en': "Best papaya milk dessert in Singapore.\nSuper yummy can't find anything better when one is craving for papayas with milk. Don't think yellow!"}

author: Alicia B
description: {'en': "The massive line always terrifies me- I avoid weekend and friday nights at all costs. Not sure how they source their grass jelly but its texture is so incredible and maybe slightly firmer? or has an extra bite as compared to everywhere else that I've had it. Obsessed with the grass jelly + mixed fruits."}

author: Jason W
Sherly Widjaya
description: {'en': 'Best dessert place in my opinion. All the desserts taste just right. Not too sweet not too bland, just nice. Mango sago is fav.\nExpect long and never ending queue when visiting bugis outlet, even on weekday. Weekend probably worse. But the queue moved quite fast tho. Just be patient to get your seat.'}

author: Victoria Anne U
description:
{'en': 'First time here
I often walk pass Liang seah street, and it‚Äôs often crowded. Lucky for us, it wasn‚Äôt too busy so finally had the chance to try.

Had 3 items which amounted to 16.20 which is not too bad. May be on the pricier side.
The desserts were very rich and Gao, and very shiokkk.

Definitely understand the hype around it.
Service was also very fast. Overall, definitely enjoyed.'}

author: Daphne
description: {'en': 'The ordering system doesn‚Äôt work at the table so you have to go to the counter, order and pay. Other than that, it was a good experience!\n\nWe got honeydew watermelon sago, orh nee and a steamed egg and ginger juice. Highly recommend the steamed egg and ginger juice!!!!'}

author: Putri Utami Ruswandi
description: {'en': "At night looking for dessert, you can try coming here.  Various hot and cold desserts are available.  it's just that you have to be prepared to queue, especially on weekends.  the price for 2 courses is around S$10, I tried mango pomelo and black bean.  Mango pomelo must be tried, it's really delicious"}

author: RH Ong
description: {'en': 'Super delicious flavour bomb dumplings and noodles cooked to perfection! Flavours are all on the heavier side but these are some\nBold favours I really enjoyed! Will highly recommend and for sure will be back!'}

author: Wei Qian (Sandy)
ms __
description: {'en': 'Ordered the set of 5 dumplings, and out of the five flavours, the fried pierogi and quail quail duck were the standouts. The Sichuan pork noodles were also packed with flavour and had a great spicy kick‚Äîloved it! Highly recommend making a reservation, as seats are limited and it‚Äôs a popular spot. Service crew was warm and friendly making it an enjoyable dining experience.'}

author: Kai Ling
description: {'en': 'The place filled up fast on a weekday evening when I went. Nice vibes, friendly staff. Prawn and crab dumpling was juicy and filled with plump prawn meat. Noodles were soo good. Super satisfied with a glass of ice cold beer to go woth the tasty meal.'}

author: S F
description: {'en': 'Great food and ambience. Dumplings and noodles were simply scrumptious. The cold beer was fruity amd delicious. Definitely worth a visit. Price is reasonable too.'}

author: Dani
description: {'en': 'A must when in Singapore üåütheir lunch special is super worth it. My faves are the sichuan pork noodles and sichuan dumplings, so tasty and just the right type of spice! (Fried pierogi is a good fried option too.)'}

author: Kearney Tan (Kearney Tan)
description:
{'en': 'Came on a Monday night at 7pm.
Had to wait till everyone arrive to be seated, but ofcourse if your party is arriving soon the staff is kind enough to let you sit and order first.

Order many things, mostly were mediocre but what stood out were the 2 photos here. The Spicy Sichuan Dumplings and the Quail Quail Duck.

Must try!'}

author: Jie Ru Chan
description:
{'en': 'Yummy food as always!

Highly recommend their noodles - cooked to perfection, very flavourful and amazing textures beautifully combined. I probably tried all their noods and my fav would be the spicy Sichuan and this prawn because the ebiko üëåüèªüëåüèªüëåüèª

Dumplings are good too (of course) but be sure to eat it fresh! But still would recommend the noodles over dumplings.

Very consistent throughout the outlets as well (CQ, Amoy)'}

author: Abilaa
description: {'en': 'The food was amazing and I feel that it‚Äôs quite reasonably priced for CBD area! It was about $9 per bowl of noodle. The place can be a little cramped and small but the food and service makes up for it! Highly recommend: Miso Mushroom Noodles, Braided Pork Noodles, Fried Pierogi Dumplings and UME Dream (Drink)'}

author: YQ Lau
description: {'en': 'Ordered the dumpling platter of 15 which allowed you to try various flavors and the dried pierogi was really good that we ordered more of it. We had XO prawn noodles and miso mushroom noodles too, both of which were nice. The restaurant was a bit small so do make reservation in advance to avoid disappointment!'}

author: Chloe Rachel
description: {'en': "Came here for dinner. They take reservations, and diners can also use the QR code at the restaurant to place their order. Food is affordable and plated beautifully, especially the dumplings! Innovative menu. The pickled black fungus (appetizer) came in a huge bowl for only $2. Also had their smoked duck dumplings and braised pork noodles. They were both flavourful and different than regular pork offerings! We sat at the bar. Table seating is rather tight in a small area. My grapefruit thyme green tea took awhile to come (it came after all the food had arrived), so it's possible they forgot the order. However, would still highly recommend as the food was tasty and creative."}

author: pam
description: {'en': 'Went on a Sunday evening at around 7pm ! Managed to get a table for 2 but seating is slightly limited without a reservation and the table we got was a little small, but in the end we managed to get a bar seat before my friend and I ordered. Really cozy vibe and most of the people there were on dates or catching up with friends ! We ordered and shared the miso mushroom noodles, braised pork noodles, original and smoked duck dumplings ! Personally, we really recommend the miso mushroom noodles and the original dumplings !! The braised pork noodles may be a little salty but not too jelak. My friend loveddd the original dumplings so much she ordered a second round ! You should really give this place a go as a first date and it‚Äôs about less than $30 for a set of dumplings and a bowl of noodles ! Would love to go back for the lunch deal !'}

author: Cheyenne Koh
description: {'en': 'Space is slightly small so it‚Äôs not very friendly for more than 4 pax but the food is really sumptuous and filling. Affordable for what it is as well!'}

author: Jarome Ng
xuanni
description: {'en': 'The food was excellent, my fav would be the sichuan noodles and the fried pierogi dumplings. The food will turn cold very fast cause i think the place was too cold but other than that alls good'}

author: Hc Ng
description:
{'en': '‚≠êÔ∏è 4.7/5 Food
‚≠êÔ∏è 5/5 Service

Ordered the braised pork noodle, dumpling platter, and dessert dumpling.

‚≠êÔ∏è Highly recommend the braised pork noodle. Shredded pork done well, juicy, tender and flavorful. Not dry like some other shredded pork I‚Äôve had. Noodles done well too, not overcooked and still bouncy. Soy tare sauce had the perfect blend of sweet and salty flavors. Overall, every flavor complemented one another.

‚≠êÔ∏èOne of my favorite dumplings was the Karana Momo dumpling. I‚Äôll be real, I‚Äôm not a big herbivore, but this vegetarian dumpling really stood out to me amongst the other meat-based dumplings. The ingredients were fresh and all the flavors fell into place. I wanted to steal one more from my vegetarian friend üò≥.

‚≠êÔ∏èThe Fried Pierogi dumpling was another one I really liked. I generally like all the ingredients on their own already so this dumpling being one of my favorites was no surprise. A very delicious savory dumpling, but if you don‚Äôt like truffle, it has truffle potato so beware! (but the truffle taste isn‚Äôt very strong)

üëçüèª The other dumplings like Original, Veggie mandu, and smoked duck, were alright. Nothing too outstanding about it in my opinion. Dough was smooth with a good ratio of filling to dough. Fillings were fresh as well, but the combination didn‚Äôt stand out to me. Still good nonetheless!

üëçüèªDessert dumpling was pretty good, I could really taste the pear in it. The Amaretto made the dumpling quite fragrant overall. Although I don‚Äôt see myself ordering it again, but it‚Äôs definitely worth trying once!

‚≠êÔ∏èService was excellent! Servers were very friendly and fun! Talked us through the whole menu when I asked them what do they recommend.

üî• In a nutshell, great noodles and dumplings! Highly recommend you to visit this restaurant!'}

author: M Astro
description: {'en': 'Corporate order. The interior looks nice and eclectic. Food was good too despite being a takeout. Would love to visit to dine in again someday.'}

author: Leslie Lim
description: {'en': 'I love the aesthetic of the restaurant, from the cute menus to how the food is presented! The noodles were amazing but I thought the braised pork was a bit on the dry side. The plant-based dumplings are also perfectly spiced! Decent portions and an amazing iced drink on a hot day. Would come again!'}

author: Cheetah paws (Cheetahpaws)
description: {'en': 'The noodles and dumplings are delicious. The duck and original dumplings are tasty. Prawn & crab can be quite heavy taste and fresh if you like. Love the atmosphere, sat at the bar, lucky we could walk in during saturday without reservations for 2 pax.'}

author: Kasia Thacker
description: {'en': 'Friendly service, eaay to order menu, prompt food to table. Nice to sit outside and enjoy the happenings along the street. Popular place, so either book or get here early. PS: opens 5.30pm, not 5pm as Google currently has it'}

author: Dan P
description:
{'en': 'This lil‚Äô shop on Amoy St is serving up tasty lunch sets for the hungry worker!

I don‚Äôt work in the city anymore but was here for a meeting around lunchtime so decided to wander down Amoy and see what was on offer. Many old faves have since moved on - a sign of the recent times - but this place caught my eye so decided to check it out.

Went for the braised pork noodles and smoked duck dumpling set and wasn‚Äôt disappointed. Very attractively plated food that had bags of flavour! It also comes with a drink for under $20 so nicely priced for the area. You can also customise your order, with various add-ons available.

Place was full around 2pm when I visited, but the tables turnover pretty quickly so you probably don‚Äôt have too long of a wait even if you get here during peak times.'}

author: Adrian Chan
description: {'en': 'Interesting take of chinese and japanese noodles and dumplings. There are many flavours of dumplings to choose from - personally like the prawn and crab dumpling. The drink was also very refreshing and perfect for the hot weather. We had the lunch set, which I think was a good deal. Definitely recommended to try. We came on a weekday lunch time and the place was almost full, but was lucky enough to get a table after a few mins.'}

author: Ming
description: {'en': '[Edited] It was so good I went back the next day for lunch :D\n\nHad the $16 set lunch and it was so good. Noodles were well cooked and portion was just nice. Generous with the ingredients. Grapefruit green tea was refreshing and not too sweet. Dumplings were really good. Favourites are fried pierogi and original ones. Definitely coming back for my dumplings fix!'}

author: CoolBeans
description: {'en': 'had an amazing time here at dumpling darlings, where the employees were very hospitable!! highly recommend the fried pierogi and braised pork :)'}

author: W
melondamien foo
description: {'en': 'Great little restaurant offering interesting variations of dumplings and noodles. We ordered a dumplings platter that came with all their dumplings, 3 each for a total of 15 i think. Besides the classic ones, they also had impossible meat with curry flavour, vege, duck and a few others. Also ordered XO prawn noodles and braised pork noodles. Everything was good. Dumplings flavourful and did not require any vinegar dip. Noodles slightly bland for my liking as i prefer much more savoury taste.\n\nPlace was small so reservations essential. Aircon might have been broken as it was really hot. Not a large menu so probably wont be back too soon'}

author: MNG
description:
{'en': 'Hippy joint with a great vibe, reminding me of Melbourne.

It uses a QR code ordering system. Small selection but well thought out menu.

Restaurant was packed during lunch. Both ala carte and set menus are available which the latter offers options of noodles and dumplings.

Spicy Sichuan dumplings were of moderate heat yet tasty.

Sichuan pork noodles was a tad too mild for my liking. The minced pork was on the lean side. Noodle was cooked al dente which was very good.

Its salted plum wolfberry pu-erh was a show stopper. Very balanced with a generous touch of plum and wolfberry. Refreshing and addictive.'}

author: Goh
description:
{'en': 'Delicious noodles and dumplings. Smoked Duck, Pierogi, and Momo were my favourite dumplings. Their side dish is free-flow, and are a great addition to your noodles.

Beverages are refreshing- Longan Osmanthus and Passionfruit Ginger Soda

Great atmosphere, great service.

Definitely worth the calories and price.'}

author: Alexander Aaltonen
Cristina Ng
description:
{'en': 'A cozy restaurant with quality dumplings!

I felt super welcomed, after being seated, the waiter served us the complimentary side dish of bean sprouts and shredded carrots, refreshing!

Ordered 2 lunch set and it comes with a bowl noodles, a choice of their dumplings, and a drink.

We ordered:
-XO prawn noodles (prawns are super fresh)
-Prawn and crab dumplings
-Fried Pierogi dumplings (my favourite! Didn‚Äôt know potato dumplings tasted so good)
-Longan Osmanthus pu-erh drink (highly recommend)
-Passion fruit ginger soda (ginger taste is super strong)

Overall, food is great and price point wise is affordable. Lunch set is definitely value for money.'}

author: littlebitofnoms
description:
{'en': 'A dim-lit moody eatery with a fresh and unique twist on traditional dumplings, and the most delicious egg noodles!!

What we tried:

Dumplings

ü•ü The Original (10/10)
[ minced pork collar, ginger soy sauce, napa cabbage, black vinegrette ]
This was an elevated and upgraded version of traditional fried dumplings, with its thin and crispy skin and delicious pork filling! Definitely one of the best gyoza-style dumplings I‚Äôve ever tried, and you can‚Äôt go wrong with ordering this! The dipping ginger vinegar sauce provided tastes 10/10 when paired together. It‚Äôs so good no wonder dumplings are in their name!

ü•ü Fried Pierogi (9.5/10)
[ Smoked bacon, truffle potato, caramelised onion, cheddar, sriracha crema ]
Wow, now this was unique and unexpectedly tasty! The dumpling has slightly thicker and crunchier skin, and a generous amount of potato filling, with some bacon bits and hints of truffle. There‚Äôs a little cheddar in it as well, and overall this was an excellent savoury dish! Definitely worth giving a try for its unique and fresh taste profile. The accompanying dip is a sriracha cream-like sauce, which had a subtle kick of sriracha spice in the aftertaste. I however wasn‚Äôt a big fan of the sriracha cream dip, and liked it better without. Without the sauce, the dumplings have generally no spice, and can be enjoyed by children. Personally, while I did thoroughly enjoy the pierogis, I think their original dumplings fared a little better..!

ü•ü (dessert dumpling) Pear and Cheese (11/10)
[ amaretto, cream cheese, vanilla bean, poached pears, served with tasmanian honey ice cream ]
Now this is a must order! Highly recommend trying their creative dessert dumplings, I don‚Äôt think you can find this anywhere else! Very well executed taste profile, and all the flavours and textures blended beautifully. The dumplings have generous amounts of warm pear bits, and when enjoyed with the ice cream became a fun play of temperatures. These honey ice cream was very refreshing and went very well with the texture of the crunchy dumpling skin, too. So good. ü•π They truly were out of this world!

Egg Noodles

üçú Braised Pork Noodles (11/10)
[ pork ragu, soy tare, bacon sofrito, fried shallot, spring onion ]
This was incredible. I am usually picky with noodles but this surprisingly hit the spot.. much better than I had expected, and I would come back just for the noodles!! The egg noodles had the perfect chewy texture, and the braised pork ragu was so satisfyingly delicious. Ingredients were so generous and I like that they give you a full hanjuku egg! These braised pork noodles somehow remind me of Taiwanese Mazesoba, but without the spice. The addition of fried shallots (commonly seen in Indonesian cuisine) was a very smart one, adding crunch and slight sweetness to the noodles. The fried shallots were slightly bigger than the usual size, and I really liked that extra touch! Ultimately, I really enjoyed everything about these egg noodles! The portion was just right, if you are a small eater you can share this. Highly recommend.

üçú Sichuan Pork Noodles (8/10)
[ Spicy minced meat, sichuan tare, bacon sofrito, fried shallot, spring onion ]
This was pretty similar to the braised pork noodles, except with an added sichuan mala flavour minus the spice. Very little spiciness added so if you‚Äôre a sichuan noodle purist you might not enjoy this much. Nevertheless, I think it was pretty good too, but still prefer the braised pork noods.

The space is moody, with small tables quite close to one another. The place opens for dinner at 5.30pm and when we came on a Saturday at around dinnertime there were not much people, but the crowd started coming in at around 6.30~ so I recommend coming a bit earlier. Service was quick and our food was served in under 7 minutes upon placing our order. Overall, a great modern fusion restaurant and I would highly recommend trying their noodles and dumplings, especially the dessert ones!! They‚Äôve really perfected their recipes and I love the concept! (Also love their super adorable menu!)

food 5/5
service 5/5
ambience 4.5/5'}

author: Ms Wong
Ben Cho
description: {'en': 'We had a quick dinner here. Be sure to make reservations before coming down. There is also a limit of 45m dining time.\nNoodles is good and so are the dumplings. The braised pork noodle and the original dumplings are highly recommended!'}

author: Kim Ricafort
description: {'en': 'amazinnnggg food is definitely an understatement. the noodles and dumplings are cooked to perfection. so savoury! ü•ü they had a great lunch set at $17, and it was super worth it. i got the xo prawn noodles with the original dumplings. just wish the prawns came peeled, it was quite troublesome to peel with chopsticks and a ceramic spoon.\n\nthe ambience is really nice, dim and cozy. can get a little loud when there are a lot of people in the compact space. overall, highly recommended if you‚Äôre in the area!'}

author: Kent Lin
description: {'en': "Truly a Darling! The food is phenomenal‚Äîeach dumpling is packed with flavor and cooked to perfection. The variety on the menu ensures there's something for everyone. What really stands out, though, is the exceptional staff. They are incredibly welcoming and attentive, making the dining experience even more enjoyable. Highly recommend the smoked duck dumplings! Will definitely be returning soon."}

author: J C
description: {'en': "Great noodle and dumpling. Especially the sichuan pork noodle and pierogi fried dumpling. It's a must try!!! The lunch set is ard 18+ for one bowl of noodle, 4 dumpling of 1 flavour and 1 drink! Super filling and worth it. Definitely recommend you to give it a try. Do make reservations if u are planning to dine there during peak period."}

author: Kelly Wang
description: {'en': 'Come to this restaurant very often, $17 with dumplings+noodles+drink. This branch is small so I recommend group less than 4 pax come over together.'}

author: Jan Ng
Marc Ha
description: {'en': 'Love the vibe at this small, tight-seating restaurant. Wife and I are vegetarians and were pleased with the options available - we had the miso mushroom noodles, Impossible curry dumplings and veggie mandu, all of which were delicious. They were very generous with the ingredients (chives, mushrooms, seaweed) in the noodles. The yuzu osmanthus drink was also really good.'}

author: T Ong
Ruth Go
description: {'en': "Delicious dumplings and noodles. The dumpling varieties are interesting, a mixture of classics and creative ones. The noodles are more notable for me though, they're really freakin tasty, the umami is undeniable.\nThe space is small with limited seatings, so it's worth placing a reservation beforehand since they're almost always full."}

author: Yulong Lin
description:
{'en': 'Good dumplings, decent noodles and drinks. We tried the lunch deal, consisting of 4 dumplings, a bowl of noodles and a drink.

The flavours in the prawn and crab dumplings worked surprisingly well, unlike what I had at a previous dumpling restaurant. The dumplings were a little spicy and the prawns weren't too fresh but that's not unusual in Singapore. We also tried the spicy Sichuan dumplings, which were decent but I felt like maybe there was a bit too much going on in the dumplings. It would be good to note that the dumplings had more flavours than you would usually expect from Chinese dumplings, and the spicy Sichuan dumplings didn't have the "ma" (numbing) sensation you may expect.

The braised pork noodles were decent, although the pulled pork was a little dry. They also provided unique drinks like Grapefruit Thyme Strawberry Green Tea, which nicely completed the meal.

They were attentive and offered us a new facemask when they noticed one of us dropped a facemask on the floor. We went there at noon on a weekday and it was quite full. We waited for 20 minutes to get a seat, and couldn't stay much longer than 1h as they had other customers to serve. While it was full, it wasn't too noisy for a conversation, so it can be a good spot for catching up with one or two friends.'}

author: Jo T
Jing G.
Jun Wei
description: {'en': "This was a very special dining experience! Dumpling darlings really added a new dimension to dumplings with bold but delicious new flavours. The noodles were well portioned and very palatable and the cherry on top for me was the complimentary appetiser (not shown here) and the great service staffs! Looking forward to my next visit.\n\nEdit: went back again, and I have to say they're really consistently good. This time Im adding photos of their appetiser, which I really enjoyed a lot! Their noodles are also all impressive, I'm sure I'll be back a lot more. Just note that because they're quite busy, there's a limited dine in time of 45mins so it's not a place to sit down and catch up but you can definitely find a place for that in the area."}

author: Dayrius Tay Jiale
description: {'en': 'Fusion dumplings with western and Japanese influences. Primarily patronized by caucasians. Innovative take on dumplings- there‚Äôs jackfruit dumplings that taste like prata, smoked duck dumplings that taste like bacon and a few other random flavors. Very small place with prompt service'}

author: Yingying
description: {'en': 'No doubt one of the best dumplings i have tried. They have many unique dumplings e.g pierogi. Both service and food was excellent. You probably need to reserve if you are trying to visit at night because it gets really crowded.'}

author: Smilinglilwen
description: {'en': 'Tiny cozy corner for a light meal! Did not order the noodles to be able to try more kinds of gyoza (: Each selection was paired with different unique sauces and platings were awesome!'}

author: Haritha Jayagopi
description: {'en': 'Wow ordered from them 2 times via foodpanda and it‚Äôs so worth it. The Sichuan noodles are great, ample amount and not too spicy. Also the pierogi dumplings are so interesting to eat, the sauce to dip is excellent and has a wonderful tang to it! Always a satisfying meal, and it comes packed beautifully!'}

author: Ailsa Kuan
description:
{'en': "Recommended by my friend as well as Time Out Singapore. We came on a weekday during lunch time at about 11:20am. Seats are limited I would say about 20+ to 30 people max. They have counter seats as well as normal dining tables.

Opening hours for lunch is from 11am - 3pm but I would say at about 12:20pm the place was packed and you probably would not be able to get seats so do come early!

The aesthetics here are fantastic. Its quite dimly lit so it really gives off a chill vibe and the menu is exceptionally cute! I love it!

We went for the lunch set as well as their all day 2 for $20 draft beers for Valentine's (might end soon).

Lunch set is at $17 and for that price you get one noodle, an iced drink as well as one of the dumpling types. Since I was there with a friend we decided to get different things so we could try out more.

For the noodles I got the Sichuan pork noodles which was exceptionally yummy and my friend got the miso mushroom. I personally really enjoyed the pork noodles. It wasn't overwhelmingly spicy. Just the right amount of kick. If you want it even spicier you can request for chilli oil and they will give it to you.

For the dumplings we ordered spicy sichuan and fried pierogi. My personal fave was the fried pierogi. Although it has fried bacon, truffle potato, caramelised onion and cheddar I could mainly taste the potato which I love. Its served on top of a dollop or Sriracha crema. I could eat 10 of these and still want more.

Drinks wise I went for the longan osmanthus pu erh and I love it! Very refreshing and really comes with longan bits and jelly in the drink. Also its a tall glass so its worth it too.

Draft beer was quite interesting we went for the dragon fruit beer and I forgot the other one but both were pleasant! Also wanted to commend the staff here, all very on the ball and gave great service!

All in all I would say I'd definitely be back for more here!"}

author: Sherine Chng
description: {'en': 'Really good dumplings and noodles! You have to order their appetisers - pickled black fungus and bean sprout! I love love their prawn and crab dumplings! Price is super reasonable too. Highly recommend this place!'}

author: jayjesse02
description:
{'en': "Best. Dumplings. Ever.

author: Mark Tho
description:
{'en': 'OMG!!! How good are the dumplings here!?

author: Orrdii Tan
description: {'en': 'This place definitely made it to the list of my top noodles restaurants in Singapore! Both the miso mushroom and sichuan pork noodles were fantastic!!
