Awesome vibe here with friendly service. Highly recommended! ‚ù§Ô∏è'}

author: Mariateresa Signorile
description: {'en': 'This cute place was a random choice one night and it was really a great experience! We had to wait for a while, like 20 mins to get a table because it was very packed and we didn‚Äôt have a reservation but in the end we got the table and service was very nice! Staff is nice and attentive, food is delicious! We tried noodles which were very good and then I had vegetarian gyozas (there are two types), one of the two after a few gyozas is a bit nauseating as it has cinnamon in it but the taste is very nice and peculiar! You can tell that the gyoza dough is made fresh by them! They have also nice cocktails (very pricey, 20 dollars) and very delicious artigianal beers (for 8 dollars), very recommended!'}

author: Ann Tay
description: {'en': 'Love the variety of dumplings in this unique place that also sells Onsen egg wth Prawn noodles. Please bring wet tissues along. Better to make reservations before you go unless you want to dine after 8.30 pm.  I was told they sell deep freeze dumplings to go. There is a menu to try all 10 types of dumplings so we choose that. Serve by a young team & seriously on a week night they were booked full till after 8+!!'}

author: Peng Siang
description: {'en': 'Came here on  Sunday evening and was lucky to be able to get a seat promptly. Ordered the prawn & crab dumpling which was really good, the filling was fresh and delicious! The miso mushroom noodles and sichuan noodles were good too! Oh and the grapefruit thyme green tea is a must order!\nThe service staff were also prompt and alert although we were seated outside.'}

author: Dani Rodr√≠guez Navidad
description: {'en': 'Such a great discovery! I went there a couple of times during mu stay in SG and I would have gone again if I had more time! First time I ordered the dumpling mix, so delicious flavours!\nSecond time I definetely had to go for the noodles and the special chicken dumplings!\nFruity drinks are also a must!'}

author: Stephanie C
description: {'en': 'Lunch sets are great here; comes with a choice of noodle, dumplings and a fancy nonalcoholic drink of sorts at $16! And also bean sprout x carrot to start. Short wait for a table as a result of Covid and WFH situations.\n\nTheir dinner is worth a visit too - love their desserts and carrot gin!'}

author: Chin Zhi Hui
description: {'en': 'The dumplings here were delicious and they avoided the overly oily taste profile.  drinks had real longan and herbal bits and were not lame.  But the best was the pear dumpling desserts which we did not expect.  service was chirpy as well!'}

author: Casper Liew
description: {'en': 'Good food; reservations are best.45mins dining time/table due space constraint.Set lunch $16 worth considering; 1 noodle,1 type of dumpling and a cold beverage.Staff are courteous and helpful.'}

author: Wen Huang
description: {'en': 'The dumplings (and noodles) here are worth multiple revisits. Try the pierogi, original, or impossible, to start. The lunch set (~$17) is a good deal as you get your choice of a noodle, dumpling, and a drink.'}

author: Jun Jie Soo
description: {'en': 'Delicious dumplings and noodles! The staff are also very attentive! There were some smokers outside at the next door restaurant where their smoke came to Dumpling Darlings. I made an offhand remark and a staff promptly went next door to give feedback. She then came over to ask if we were okay. The attentiveness was heartening! Very positive experience! Would recommend anyone to drop by to have their noodles and dumplings :)'}

author: Samuel Swee
Xiu Jin Guo
Anh Thu
description: {'en': 'Amazing food. Highly recommend the set of 5 different kinds of dumplings (3 pieces/each) and Sichuan egg noodle. The place can be super busy at night so you should come early and book in advance. In overall, I had great experience here.'}

author: KC
description: {'en': 'Reasonably priced and rather tasty albeit it being a simple menu. Their offerings  are not for dumpling or gyoza purists though, as even the original has sauce slathered on it pre-serving. the prices are very reasonable as well. I do wish they serve rice and some larger dumplings sans sauce for those who prefer the classic style of eating gyoza.'}

author: Pramila Ghode
description: {'en': 'Super delicious vegetarian dumplings... the flavours are unique and keep you craving for more. The dipping sauces taste complimented the dumplings really well. The place is quite small but staff is accommodating and friendly. Service was pretty fast too... will definitely visit again'}

author: Chen Zhi Lin
description:
{'en': 'I was introduced to this place by my Friend and we used Burpple Beyond for this meal.

We dined as a 6 pax so we decided to get one of each dumpling flavour since we could get 6 set lunches. Each set lunch came with a drink and 4 dumplings as a complimentary side dish.

I really liked the miso mushroom noodles as it was really tasty and went well with the dumplings. The passionfruit sofa ginger soda was really refreshing too, which really helps especially since the Singapore weather has been quite unforgiving of late.

My top three favourite dumplings has to be the fried pierogi, the smoked duck and the original flavours.

Vegetarian and Vegan friends will be happy to know that they can dine here as they have vegan options as well :)'}

author: Natasha Angeline
description: {'en': 'Good food and good customer service. This place deserves a 5-star review. Singapore is known for their bad customer service but this place is different. The staff are friendly despite non-stop crowds flowing in. The ale is nice. The dumpling set is perfect for 3 people (3 dumplings each for 5 flavours). The price is very reasonable too. I only spent $25.5 for my orders - 1 glass of ale, 1 dumpling set and 2 bowls of pork noodle shared between the 3 of us.'}

author: Angie Ling
description: {'en': "Have been wanting to try the dumplings here ever since they opened. Finally. First try. The menu was very simple. They have 6 varieties of dumplings, but the dumplings platter only have 5 types. My favourite was the fried pierogi which consist of potato, bacon and truffle. The noodles were not too bad either. Though it's rather a small bowl, but I love the generous serving of shallots."}

author: feodor mak
TheFitnessTheory
description: {'en': "Went there for dinner- we had the dumplings platter to try all of their flavours and shared a bowl or pork noodles. Everything was very good (the noodles were a bit greasy maybe but that's it) and the seychuan dumplings are too die for.\nThe venue gets crowded at night so make sure you reserve if you don't want to queue outside (very limited seats inside, which makes the venue very cosy and intimate)\nThe staff was overwhelmed but I'm guessing it's just due to the fact the venue is super new. Keep on the great work guys!"}

author: serene soon
description: {'en': 'My mind is blown, holy smokes. Darling, dumplings, darling ‚ù§Ô∏è every single flavor slapped me out to outer space. Wat in the dumpling heaven, if you wanted to try the best dumplings money can buy, look nowhere else.'}

author: Dawn Lim
description: {'en': 'The set lunch is really value for money and includes a bowl of noodles, a side of dumplings, and a drink. The noodles, dumplings and drinks all come in different flavour so there‚Äôs something for everyone. Yummy food, tasteful drinks and fun atmosphere!'}

author: Jordon Ho
description: {'en': 'The overall experience was great! Although the staff was a bit overwhelmed by the crowd, they managed to get us a sit. Tried smoke duck dumplings with Miso mushroom noodles. Smoke duck dumplings, filled is packed with Lup Cheong which gave an interesting texture and uniqueness to the dumplings. Paired with the pickled onions, it provides an acidity to cut through the fat in the dumplings. Awesome!'}

author: Tiek
description:
{'en': 'AMAZING ! If you are in town and looking at eating the best of the best dumplings , we recommend Dumpling Darling ü•ü

I would definitely recommend booking in advance because it can get very busy and difficult to find a table. However it is still possible ! Indeed we got luck last night and had the opportunity to eat at the bar.

Cocktails were fantastic, we recommend sharing the dumpling discovery (set of 15) and a bowl of home made egg noddles. Everything is affordable and very reasonably priced.

Anyway you can‚Äôt go wrong with this place. Everything is well taken care of with details everywhere. We loved the menu , why not more places are doing this ? The drawings are fantastic üòçüòç it makes the experience so much more enjoyable.

Congrats to the team and everyone involved. If we were not living on the other side of the planet , this would be our favourite spot in town.'}

author: Mark Yeo
description:
{'en': "Absolutely delicious dumplings that the local hipster would approve as much as the American missing their pot stickers.
Had a plate of the original and it was just too good to explore the other funky flavours.
So, it looks like I'll just have to go back for more.
The carbs are worth a mention too!"}

author: Joanne Yap
description: {'en': "Came here for dinner on a friday night. There were long queues even after 8pm that the staff had to nicely chase us after we finished eating. So I'd say it's not the best place to sit and catch up with your friends over dinner & drinks.\n\nHave to try their dumplings! They sell their dumplings separate from their noodles. Cold brew tea was nice too."}

author: Ben Gan
description: {'en': 'Cosy modern take on dumplings. It‚Äôs a little bit tight for space inside this joint but the food is pretty tasty. We had the sample platter which had a selection of 5 types of dumplings and is enough for 2 when combined with a bowl of noodles each. The beansprout starters are a nice touch addition but it can get pretty busy.'}

author: Jas Explores
description: {'en': 'Perfect place to grab a lunch or dinner with colleagues or friends! Their dumplings and set lunches are really delicious and make great dishes to go along with beer or other cold beverages. However, since there aren‚Äôt many seats available, it‚Äôs better make a reservation beforehand. Of course, you can always walk in and just wait for roughly 20-30 minutes during rush hours, too. Highly recommend this place!'}

author: nina e
description: {'en': 'It was my first time at this outlet and I enjoyed the dumplings very much. They were as delicious as the ones from the circular branch. The service was speedy and friendly too.'}

author: Wilson L
description: {'en': "Love the food here. The dumplings are really well-made and flavorful. There's a variety of different tastes as well.\n\nGot a bowl of noodles to make sure the meal feels full too!"}

author: Valerie Kim
description: {'en': 'the dumplings were amazing and the male server jj was really nice and accommodating to us!! highly recommend the fried pierogi and veggie mandu!! the sichuan noodles with lime the highlight!!!!! üòçüòçüòç'}

author: edwin
description: {'en': 'You get flavorful food, great service and even the cosy evening atmosphere of a bar at incredible prices. I enjoyed the taste and variety of the dumplings they offer, yet, surprisingly, I liked their noodles even more. One of my best local recommendations.'}

author: Anissa Sariatu
description: {'en': "The awesome dumplings still taste awesome as always. Try the party platter! The mushroom miso noodle isn't bad either.\n\nOne thing we wish them to improve is the queueing process. We were queueing and got told that we were next in line (no 001 in the app notification) however we waited got 25+ mins with some random groups of ppl just cutting the line, getting into the restaurant and when we complained to the attendant, he just told us 'sorry about that'. Seriously pls manage your booking system better."}

author: Shandy L.
description: {'en': "The pierogi dumplings are my fav! The smoked duck dumplings are more ordinary. The iced passionfruit ginger soda adds a refreshing touch to the entire meal. Reservations are recommended as they're usually booked out."}

author: Stephanie Ong
description: {'en': 'Expect to queue! Went for dinner on a Friday night and there were about 7 groups in front of us. Space is quite tight but the food is really value for money and quite delicious. Love the variety of dumplings available and the service was excellent too. Overall great vibe but more suitable for smaller groups or couples.'}

author: Yukino Angela
Cecilia MJKW
description: {'en': 'Delicious food served very quickly. Mushroom ramen was excellent and the duck dumplings were superb. Passion fruit and ginger juice washed it all down splendidly.'}

author: Ashlyn
Nathaniel Tan
description: {'en': 'Had one of their $17 set lunches and it was great! Had the mushroom miso noodle, the pereigo dumplings and a drink (can‚Äôt remember). Service from JX (really nice bigger boy$m) was excellent. Will come back again, If not for the food, to say hi to JX! Thanks mate'}

author: Jackie
description: {'en': 'Absolutely enjoyed our lunch set (with burpple beyond we paid $20 nett for 2 sets of noodles, dumplings and drinks ). The mushroom miso noodles is great, abeit miso taste is missing, taste more like bak chor mee. The szechuan noodles is nice too, not spicy at all though - you will either rejoice or frown depending on if you are a spicy lover. Dumplings are really nice too. I tried the original one but would love to try the momo curry or smoked duck nett. I have no complaints of this place amd since its near my office i might come often.'}

author: Neo Hui Ying
description: {'en': 'Reached the area before its opening at 6pm on a Friday night. They quickly served us after spraying some hand sanitiser on our hands. We decided to order the platter where we had 5 different flavours, with 3 dumplings, suitable for us as we had 3 pax. We also ordered Miso mushroom noodles and Sichuan Pork Noodles and they were so filling!! The restaurant was definitely not stingy with their ingredients. Although with the new policies eating time is limited to 45minutes, their serving speed is quite fast and their customer service is A++. Would visit again after the virus situation dies down!'}

author: Michele Chang
description: {'en': 'The space is small, tight but stylish and comfortable. A great place which gets you yummy food which is value for money! Try getting the dumpling platter to try all flavours. The original flavour was my favourite. Their dessert dumpling was really tasty and I would order it again!'}

author: aly
description: {'en': 'thoroughly enjoyed my meal here, complimentary pickled vegetables was very refreshing! $16++ lunch set for noodles, 4 dumplings and drink is definitely worth the money. Recommend the fried pierogi, original flavoured dumplings and Sichuan flavoured egg noodles!'}

author: Kane Burnet
description: {'en': '10/10 dumplings and noodles with some great beers to go with it - worth a visit in the Amoy area'}

author: Jerin Lee
description: {'en': 'Came here for dinner without reservation on a Saturday evening. The waiting time was reasonable though the place is a little small. Really amazing food, we ordered the noodles and a dumpling platter. If you‚Äôre unsure of what to try first, get the platter as you get to try the different dumplings without too much of a commitment. Overall really delicious, staff seemed to really enjoy working there as well, so we really liked the vibes too. Pardon the lighting, doesn‚Äôt do the food justice :)'}

author: Samyukta Sounderraman
description: {'en': 'Highly recommend the Pierogi dumpling and the Sichuan Noodles. Food is of good quality and affordable as well. Cocktails are also well made.'}

author: YU-FENG CHEN
description: {'en': 'Friendly service and rich taste of dumpling! Can try many type of fried dumpling with a good drink. Dessert is a sweet secret ü§´ ‚Ä¶'}

author: Phang Kuang Wei
description: {'en': 'Ramen was amazing with different sides to choose from!!!!! Came here a few times already, highly recommend the sichuan pork noodles and fried pierogi'}

author: Meryl Lau
description: {'en': 'One of my favorite lunch options, love their lunch sets.'}

author: H L-J
description: {'en': 'Lovely vegetarian dumplings and staff who are really nice. Dined as a solo female traveller and was happy to eat here. Nice choice of drinks. Would recommend'}

author: ÏÑúÌóåÎçï
description:
{'en': 'Strongly recommend for who are seeking trendy Chinese dumpling and noodle.

Food:
All menus‚Äô quality was good for this price, simple and good quality

Ambience and service:
very casual and trendy ambience, it‚Äôs where hipsters go for light dinner and beers'}

author: John Dillon
description: {'en': 'Lovely and cozy place to get some awesome food. They had a good variety of unique dumplings and we ate every single one brought out in no time flat. Relatively affordable for Singapore but surely not the cheapest dumplings. They had a couple good beers on tap and overall loved my small dinner had here.'}

author: Qin Tao
description: {'en': 'I like the lunch set, main dish is noodle, with 4 pieces of dumplings, and the very creative drinks in the menus. worth the money ‚Ä¶ and very important is walk distance to have lunch..'}

author: Shella S
description: {'en': 'Bit crowded and noisy, reservations recommended. Delicious Al dente noodles and dumplings, my favourite was the Fried Perogi. Affordable prices, get the gang of 5 dim sum and you get to try all dumpling flavours. Cute branding too.'}

author: Hui Jie Heng
description: {'en': 'Everything on the menu was great! Order the sampler to try all 5 flavours. The Sichuan noodles were very good too!'}

author: k.ristenkhoo
description: {'en': 'although we went during peak hours, we managed to to get a bar seat within 5 mins ü•∞ü•∞ love their food and friendly service!! will be back to try their other dishes ü´∂üèº'}

author: Ravi Rughani
description: {'en': 'Came for late lunch as a casual walk-in as it looked like the only place that was busy around the area. The lunch menu of one noodle dish, dumpling dish, and drink is very good value for money. Had the Sichuan noodles and smoked duck dumplings- both excellent. The ginger drink is also fantastic. Highly recommend for casual dining'}

author: Kian Tat (Asian Gordon Ramsey)
description: {'en': 'Amazing place but pretty pricey for dumplings. Food was good recommend getting the original dumpling. I love the drinks especially the passion fruit.\n\nDamage $40/pax.'}

author: Pei Xuan
description: {'en': 'Ordered a bowl of braised pork noodles and 15 dumplings (party of 15) to share between myself and a friend, and paid a total of ~$16 per person. We enjoyed the noodles and found the dumplings delicious too! Would rate the dumplings as original > veggie mandu > fried pierogi > smoked duck > momo curry.\n\nService was actually great on a crowded Friday evening. Seats can be a little tight as the shop‚Äôs quite small.'}

author: Crystal Koh
description: {'en': 'Lunch set $16, but with burpple offer it‚Äôs one for one which makes it a great value set. Includes choice of one noodles, 5 dumplings and a drink. I took the braised pork noodles (flavourful and not dry) and smoked duck dumplings while my friend took Sichuan pork and fried perogi (bacon cheese truffle). Fried perogi was the bomb, I would definitely recommend it, oozing with cheese and filled with delicious pieces of bacon but yet somewhat not that sinful and not oily at all. I tried the grapefruit strawberry green tea and am pleasantly surprised with real grapefruit pulp and the blend of tastes is perfect. The safe choice is also always longan osmanthus tea.\n\nSeats are limited tho, do make a reservation if possible :)'}

author: Celest Ter
description: {'en': 'Mushroom egg noodles were dope!!! Love their original dumplings too! And the best part was the price of the dishes! Reasonable price for a place located in Amoy Street! Cocktails was nice too!'}

author: Michael Unger
description: {'en': 'Pleasantly surprised! I had the veggie dumplings and miso mushroom noodles - both great vegetarian options!\n\nDipping sauce was a great addition and the food carried very well for delivery! Reasonably priced as well. üëçüèª'}

author: Sean S
description: {'en': 'The dumplings were really good! Prices are affordable too! I would skip the noodles and just focus on the dumplings and beer!'}

author: Alexandra Long
description: {'en': 'Nice little cosy place.  Although the szechuan is pretty mild. Overall, dumplings are good.\nThe set meal includes a noodle main, dumplings and a drink.'}

author: Leong Chao Yong
description:
{'en': 'Located along Telok Ayer Street, the food that Dumpling Darlings had to offer left me wanting for more.

The Sichuan Noodles came with noodles that was slightly thicker than ramen, and had a hefty amount of scallions, seaweed, minced pork, together with a soft boiled egg (but from the fridge), and a dash of sesame and chilli powder.

Mix all ingredients well and the taste is absolutely stunning. The oil from the scallions brings out certain flavours that is mouthwatering and makes you want to order another.

Next in the menu was the dumpling platter! Consisting of 3 X Original, 3 X Veggie, 3 X Momo Curry (only at Amoy), 3 X Fried Pierogi, 3 X Smoked Duck.

Each dumpling was tantalising and fun, giving all types of tastes that delights the taste buds.

To end the dinner off, I ordered the Dessert Dumpling that consists of Amaretto, Cream cheese, Vanilla beans, Poached pears, and served with Tasmanian ice cream.

It is a wonderful combination of hot and cold with sour, savoury and sweet. It is extremely refreshing to end of the meal with the dessert, it is definitely a must-try!

Also, shout-out to the staff at Amoy Dumpling Darlings, absolute pleasure to be served by sure happy faces.

Definitely not to be missed! But as usual, try it for yourself!

Food: 5/5
Service: 5/5
Final Verdict: 5/5 Must Try!!'}

author: Ik Kin
description: {'en': 'The dumplings were good. $17++ for lunch set.'}

author: Min Tay
description: {'en': 'Unique dumplings in different flavours, good for sharing or for one‚Äôs own. The noodles were really delicious, quite a pity that I didn‚Äôt manage to snap a shot before starting on it!!'}

author: Peggy L.
description: {'en': 'we absolutely love and enjoy our dumplingsssssss!üòòü•üü•üü•üü•üü•üthanks for the free dessert, although haven‚Äôt finished allüòÖ....we bought two lovely dumplings t-shirts. just so addicted to DUMPINGS... ‚Ä¶'}

author: Grace Chow
description: {'en': 'I love this place! They have good noodles and a unique dumplings. Vegetarian option is also available. It is a small cozy space so it tends to get crowded during meal time, do make a booking or head over early.'}

author: J T
description: {'en': 'Dumplings were v nice and the staff were super friendly. GF order alr then only nibble nibble so i ate until i gonna baozha. The water was great too!'}

author: œÅ–ΩœÉ—î–≤—î —ÇŒ±–∏
description: {'en': 'the beautiful service crew by the name of Thet greeted us with a warm smile and we could feel the atmosphere . author: GABRIEL DFQ

author: ÍπÄÌòÑ

author: ElaineLim

author: Nicole Chua
description: {'en': 'Had an amazing dining experience at Dumpling Darlings. It was our first visit and we went for dinner. Food was good and tasty at a very reasonable price point. The staff nonetheless were accommodating and told us they could take back the dish. They even brought us an extra bowl to share the noodles after without us asking. Very kind of them!'}

author: Sushiliah Devi

The price of the food is so reasonable that even students can afford it.  Don‚Äôt give amiss to this eatery. ü§§'}

author: Cherlyn N
description: {'en': 'Fun food, Great service! (though waiting time can be improved.. esp if reserved tables are late)\n\nTry them all!'}

author: Jun Xiang Lau
description: {'en': "I had initially thought this was a bar but turns out it's a hidden gem for good food! They serve non-alcoholic drinks and they sure taste good. author: Jun Hong Kang
description: {'en': 'First time trying Pierogi and instantly fell in love with it. Noodles was not bad though nothing special compared to the Pierogi. Longan osmanthus drink was very fragrant and refreshing. Lunch set at $17 is a steal with a noodle, dumpling and drink.'}

description: {'en': 'Went there for dinner. Must try the spicey Sichuan dumpling and the Sichuan pork  noodles. Apart from the food, they also have a great selection of cocktails. - vegetarian: served with wing sauce and olive oil‚Äî> delicious! The best!

author: Mathilde HANROT

author: Dr. Cam-Duc Au

author: T OHIRA

author: Alice
description:
{'en': 'Great restaurant, I highly recommend it!
Two menus are available and well worth the price.

The dumplings are as delicious as the noodles!
I loved it.

The only downside is the limited seating.'}

author: Dudu
description:
{'en': 'Creative Chinese-Japanese fusion modern cuisine, the menu design is very intuitive, it is easy to match the meal you want! 
The noodles are very chewy, and the seasoning is just right, not too salty and not too greasy. I was really surprised by his seasoning when I tasted the first bite! The clean cooking method and the presentation are very pleasing to the eye. 
Our group has ordered every flavor. My favorite noodles are mushroom and Sichuan flavors. For dumplings, I like the original flavor and fried. In addition, his drinks are also made with care, refreshing and not too sweet. Overall, I highly recommend it! 
The only thing to pay attention to is that you may have to queue for a long time during peak meal times. The interface of the queuing system is not easy to understand. You always have to log in your name and mobile phone on the iPad first, and then queue in the queue. It is recommended to go to the queue a little early'}

author: Stefano Lotta
description: {'en': 'Narrow, air-conditioned space with tables and stools. Excellent and well-executed food, waiters speak fast English. The bathroom is clean, the open kitchen seems to be clean.'}

author: Alessandro Balani
description: {'en': 'I chose this little place reading the reviews on Google and taking into account that I was staying in Chinatown. I liked it right away. I ended the game with some sweet dumplings filled with pears and washed down with Tasmanian honey. Exceptional! Reasonable prices.\nGo there!'}

author: Alba A

author: Dianya Nareswari
description: {'en': 'The prawn noodles ohhhhhhhhhh'}

author: Anki
description: {'en': 'Both the dumplings and the noodles were fantastic!!\nBe sure to try the dessert dumplings as well. We were there on a Friday evening and it was very busy, so make a reservation.'}

author: Marisa
description: {'en': 'Fun bar specializing in delicious dumplings, everything I tried was delicious. A must go to this bar'}

author: Roberta Mazzini
description: {'en': 'Excellent restaurant that makes ravioli of all kinds!'}

author: youGO
description: {'en': 'I recommend it with all ten. A very tasty and pleasant change from rice ...'}

author: ÏöîÏø†Îßà
description: {'en': 'The original dumplings were the best, and the Soyou Mushroom Noodles were also good.'}

author: Francesca Bizzotto
description: {'en': "The dumplings were SPECTACULAR, especially the duck one üòç ABSOLUTELY highly recommended, I'll definitely go back. ‚Ä¶"}

author: Bego√±a Prieto
description: {'en': 'Good atmosphere, fast and excellent quality'}

author: Supakij Khomvilai
description: {'en': 'My friend recommended this cafe for coffee and food. I can say the food are awesome. Every dishes are flavorful with fresh ingredients and well cooked. I don‚Äôt have space for the coffee but I will go back again if I come to Singapore again. Please visit and try by yourself. Menu and order through the web by scanning QR on the table also payment too. Credit card accepted. Seating area are air conditioned and quite big. Enjoy!'}

author: Blue Blie
description: {'en': 'Didn‚Äôt try the drinks but the savoury menu here is really good. The tater tots (both honey butter and mentaiko) were heavenly. The kombu scone was very fragrant as it was filled with the chives.\n\nI came twice in four days.'}

author: Rachel Ng
description: {'en': 'Love the extensive drinks and food menu ‚Äî we were truly spoilt for choice! I ordered their a√ßai bowl, and it was so refreshing. Their bakes are chef‚Äôs kiss ‚Äî absolutely irresistible. We shared the Brussels sprouts (10/10) and the hot honey tater tots, which are a must-try.\nThis was my second visit and definitely won‚Äôt be my last.\nSunday brunch can get crowded, but despite the busy scene, the vibe stays relaxed and enjoyable. A real gem!'}

author: Zack Wong
description: {'en': 'A cozy spot to get your brunch fix! We did have to queue for a while. Absolutely demolished the food, house rosti and toast were both scrumptious, packed with flavour. Omelettes were cooked perfectly. However, the main STAR has to be the signature earl grey latte, amazing depth of aromatic tea flavour to soothe your quenches.'}

author: Alyssa Low
description: {'en': 'I have only been here twice but it is my favourite brunch place ever! Food is far superior to many other supposedly nice cafes (cough PS cafe).
