Ambience is great too and nestled at a corner in Chijmes. 10/10 would recommend'}

author: J Lim
description: {'en': 'Teriyaki ham and cheese is high recommended - to die for! I also would recommend the rosti with pumpkin - it‚Äôs really good. Some cafes overdid the rosti but this was still moist and scrambled eggs were perfectly done!\n\nIt was a overdued catch up and we spent about 2 hours there - we did not get chased away and our water bottles also get refilled from time to time. Great atmosphere and good service :)'}

author: Jed Lim
description: {'en': 'Great place for its ambience, QR code ordering, and BAKES. The BRUSSEL SPROUTS on their dough platter was amazing - sweet, caramelised and tasty! Their hash browns were well seasoned and the bacon was THICC\n\nWhat I got: Double shot white, Chicken Thigh with Garlic Foccacia - These were just okay - coffee could be creamier and richer, chicken could have been juicier although the sauce was decent.'}

author: BRYAN NZC
description: {'en': 'Tried their matcha latte and it was so good perfectly balanced, not overly sweet, and really smooth. I also got one of their signature lattes, and that was just as impressive, it‚Äôs not your normal latte I would say, The flavour was rich and satisfying. If I had more time, I‚Äôd definitely have dined in!\n\nThe staff were friendly and welcoming, and service was quick. Honestly, this spot stands out in the area probably one of the best places around for coffee and matcha. Plus, they serve a variety of freshly made breads daily, and they‚Äôre really worth trying too. Highly recommend!'}

author: Sarah A.
description: {'en': 'I enjoyed my visit here! I ordered the bread pudding and a hot latte. Both were great. This cafe is super clean and has tons of seating as well.'}

author: yixuan
description: {'en': 'loved the rosti and scrambled egg as always. earl grey latte was also perfect in the hot weather\n\ncan get crowded on the weekends and unfortunately the tables/seats are quite closely packed'}

author: Orrdii Tan
description:
{'en': '[Oct 2023] First time here but definitely not the last. Most of the dishes are unique to the cafe and well-thought - all the components on the plate complement each other perfectly.

Special mention - The pistachio raspberry cube was splendid - flaky buttery pastry with rich pistachio cream.

Service was fast and friendly, it was full house even at 3pm on a Saturday. Cafe doesn‚Äôt take reservations.

(Updated photos from visit in Nov 2023)'}

author: Kenneth Kor
description: {'en': 'Food is great. Coffee is also great. Both indoor and outdoor seating are available. Ordered the Chicken Burger which was decent, and also the rosti, which had the potato strips very thinly sliced. I still prefer the rosti from Marche though. Service was good and atmosphere was comfortable.'}

author: Noeldickson Ongah
description: {'en': 'Service is great. Attentive helpful as I was with a kiddo. Coffee drip was great. Hard to find nice fruity based one in sg. but this coffee fine.'}

author: WM
description: {'en': "Was there for a coffee but the service was so amazing üòç we were greeted by the friendly staff and they constantly filled out water glasses without us having to ask at all.\n\nBusy cafe and I'll definitely come back again!"}

author: JM
description: {'en': 'Really enjoyed brunch here. Everything was reasonably priced and the flavours were not what we were expecting of each item. Definitely elevated brunch'}

author: Jasmine Kan
Rachel T
description: {'en': 'Yummy food and decent portion sizes! It does get fairly crowded on the weekends, so you can expect to wait for a little while. It‚Äôs a bit harder to get service when seated outside but the inside gets quite noisy. I enjoyed the tater tots with hot honey butter!'}

author: pam
description: {'en': 'Came here when I went cafe hopping with my friend ! Omg the salmon and I loved the rosti ! My friend and I really enjoyed the food here and the ambience is great ! Can get pretty crowded too hehe'}

author: littlebitofnoms
description:
{'en': 'A homey cafe in a corner of Chijmes serving up delicious brunch and fresh bakes daily!

üåü Adzuki Mochi
Fluffy and crisp puff pastry enveloping homemade milk mochi and sweet red bean paste. Simple and delicious, each component works wonderfully together to create a light and satisfying pastry! There is crisp from the crispy layered pastry, chewiness from the mochi and smoothness from the red bean‚Äî a great play of textures and flavours! I like that they were generous with the mochi.

üåü Rosti with Roasted Pumpkin
A fantastic brunch plate with house rosti, sour cream, caramelised roasted pumpkin, creamy scrambled eggs, baby spinach, roasted herb tomato. The pan-fried rosti was ultra-thin with crisp layers and a fluffy interior. The caramelised roasted pumpkin was also unique, with a sweet savoury flavour profile! A great option for a filling brunch. Everything tasted great on its own too! It was a little greasy in the end, but not in a bad way.

üåü Iced Blueberry Rooibos Tea
Refreshing and tart with sweet and musky blueberry notes and a slight touch of acidity. The rooibos added a slight hint of smooth vanilla nuttiness!

Overall‚Äî I‚Äôd recommend for a comforting brunch if you‚Äôre searching for one in the area. The cozy atmosphere and gentle decor create a soothing ambience, one that I would come back for! They have got a wonderful in house bakery too: you can opt to have some tea and bakes if you‚Äôre not up for a full meal! I also love and look forward to their monthly specials which jazz up the menu and add a fair bit of excitement each month. üòå'}

author: Sigit Sugiarto
description: {'en': "This place is a nice and cozy brunch place to catch up, food is Greta and suitable for young families. The staff are really friendly and food is great! It's a good place for brunch.\n\nOne room for improvement is the staff could be more aware of the line outside. We waited outside for a seat but no one attended, we end up going inside to enquire. Perhaps it was busy period, so the staff was quite busy. Other than that the staff were great!"}

author: kai jie
description: {'en': 'Latte was very average and even slightly harsh so I suggest skipping the espresso machine based drinks till they change the bean used. The filter coffee I got however was excellent with great texture and fragrance tho ofc it comes down to which you pick. Pastry was also v nice however if the owners are reading this, please add an option when ordering through QR to HEAT UP the pastry. It was decent room temp but would be much much much better if it was warm. Appreciate the option to have the latte in a takeaway cup. Service was also very good, can tell the team enjoys, and is good at, working together. Cafe items (non-mains) are also fairly priced, would come again.'}

author: Natalie Diong
description: {'en': 'Such a nice new discovery in Singapore. Highly recommended for brunch and lunch! Seems family friendly too!'}

author: MRN
description: {'en': 'Came at 11am on a Friday and was seated immediately. Passion lemon pastry was delectable. Got the beef quesadilla which was decent too. Prices are on the higher end though worth it. What wowed me was really the service, and the welcoming nature of every staff. One of the best places to chill in Singapore!'}

author: Cassia A
description: {'en': 'This place is delicious, the service is amazing, and it‚Äôs quite a nice atmosphere. The toast with chilli, sausage, and scrambled eggs was superrrr good. Like really good.\nThey have Prefer Coffee! It‚Äôs a Singaporean beanless coffee brand. Super cool innovation and it‚Äôs quite yummy. They also have normal coffee.\nThere‚Äôs lots of natural light. Pastries look delicious. Vegetarian options, too. They also have healthy breakfasts like yogurt and smoothie bowls.'}

author: Jonathan Chew
description: {'en': 'Been here only for the pastries ever, and they have always been consistently delectable. The guava / kaffir lime / strawberry pastry is a staple for every visit. Would be a lot nicer if these could be heated up though, something we forgot to ask when we visited.\n\nThe staff were very warm in their interactions with us and the atmosphere is perfect for spending an afternoon in to escape from the heat.'}

author: Kalib K
description:
{'en': 'Having lived in San Diego for a few years, I feel pretty confident when it comes to reviewing Mexican food and Huevos does a great job.

We ordered the chicken chipotle quesadilla, fish tacos, and elotes. The quesadilla was excellent: packed with chicken and cheese, definitely not thin or skimpy, and nicely garnished.

The fish tacos were also solid, although the toppings were a little overpowering if you ate it blindfolded, you might not immediately guess it was fish. Still, it was a great taco overall.

My only real complaint was the elotes. For the price, getting only one cob of corn felt a little disappointing. It was grilled rather than steamed or boiled, and compared to what I‚Äôm used to, it was pretty lightly seasoned. I usually expect elotes to be dripping in butter and spices this one felt a little bare, which was a letdown since elotes are one of my favorite Mexican foods.

Overall, I can‚Äôt say anything bad about the place. I‚Äôd definitely recommend it to a friend, and it‚Äôs somewhere I‚Äôd feel confident taking a Mexican friend to as well. Bonus points for having Modelo, Jarritos, and Tapat√≠o seeing a Modelo in Singapore almost made me do a backflip.'}

author: Rachel Jia Hsin
description:
{'en': 'Absolutely coming back again‚Äîthis place is a hidden gem! Really loved the food, and it totally matched our taste, too.

We arrived right at 5pm when the doors had just opened, and there was already a queue forming. By the time we finished our meal, the line had doubled‚Äîclearly, this spot is no secret!

The Cauliflower Taco was crispy and packed with flavor‚Äîa great option even for non-veg lovers. The Birria Beef Quesadilla was incredibly satisfying, filled to the brim with juicy, well-seasoned meat‚Äîdefinitely not stingy with the portions.

As for drinks, we tried the Jamaica‚Äîit‚Äôs refreshingly sour, which I personally enjoyed, but if you‚Äôre sensitive to tangy flavors, you might want to go for something else.

On top of the great food, the staff were warm, welcoming, and attentive throughout our visit‚Äîbig thumbs up for their service.
The only downside was the cleanliness of the toilet, which could definitely use some improvement.'}

author: Jennifer Teo
description:
{'en': 'Love the food. Nice generous helping.

Food for two pax. (We packed part of the beef quesadillas cos we were too full.)

Strong recommended
Loaded nachos ($21)
Crispy thin nachos. Like it that there is a lot of stuff to eat the nachos with. It is just fork after fork of ingredients. Yummy

Birria beef ($20.50)
Good amount of tender beef..lots of cheese and onions. Top up 1.50 for the beef consomme, it brings the dish alive, the flavour intensifies.

Baja Fish Tacos ($19 for 3)
Nicely fried. Thick slice of fish. Nice.

Ok lah
Fried cauliflower bites ($11.90)
Aa the name suggest..haha I think it is ok but not wow!'}

author: Jonathan Kenichi
description: {'en': 'One of the best Mexican restaurant in Singapore. All the dishes are great but I wanted to appreciate the cheese they used on the tacos. They are excellent, elevating the tacos flavor to another level. My top pick will be Birria Beef Tacos and Tacos Gobernador. Restaurant is crowded on lunch weekends but worth to go and try eating at Huevos.'}

author: Loo Zheng Rong
description: {'en': 'Very nice Mexican food. Taco is loaded with lots of meat and sauce. Chips are crispy and thin. Fish taco is served hot and delicious. Portion of fried fish is substantial to munch on. Quesadilla with pork is also good. Mexican coke pales out in comparison. Taste like normal coke. But sold at $5. Overall damage for 3 dishes is $69. Quite expensive but worth to eat once in a while. Staff is friendly but can be more approachable with a smile. Go early to avoid queue even though there is 2 storey. Upstairs is cooler.'}

author: MY
description: {'en': 'Affordable Mexican food, great for sharing! The loaded nachos ($21) had lots of pulled pork, and the al pastor pork tacos ($13 for 2) were well seasoned but a little spicy. Tap water is free as well.\n\nThe dining limit is one hour but they didn‚Äôt chase us out (perhaps because we were one of the last customers to enter before they close for lunch break). Recommend to make reservations if you‚Äôre coming on a weekday, but there‚Äôs no reservation for weekends so we had to queue for 45 mins in the heat. The staff doesn‚Äôt come to give us an estimated waiting time either.'}

author: Kerry Wong
description: {'en': 'Our go to mexican food. Food has been consistent in terms of flavors and portions. Keep up the good work. Only thing is the Q which is understandable given the popularity.'}

author: M L
description:
{'en': 'Ordered takeaway so unfortunately not as fresh as eating there.

1. Baja fish tacos (set of 3), 6.5/10 ‚Äî too spicy, wish the flavour profile was fresher. Fish not crispy enough imo
2. Beef quesadilla, 8/10
3. Chicken quesadilla, 8/10
4. Prawn tacos (set of 2), 8/10 ‚Äî fresh tasting!
5. Loaded nachos, 8/10

Total $119 for 5 pax with leftovers. $23.40/pax'}

author: R T
description: {'en': 'This Mexican food is highly recommended. We ordered Overload Nachos, Tacos - beef and fish, pino colada, margarita. The portion is generous and quality. Overall the food and cocktail is excellent. The meal is so satisfying and will definitely return again.\nIt‚Äôs best to plan your reservation in advance, otherwise be ready to queue at least 20-40min during peak hour.'}

author: melissa lim
description:
{'en': 'Lively place at 11am!!

Had the nachos first and was actually full already üòÖ
Trinity mushroom quesadillas was delicious, well thought out. Didnt expect corn inside and it goes so well! Can be really filling.

We did not finish the tacos because we were already full from the nachos and quesadillas üåÆü§é'}

author: Riel
description: {'en': 'Was good but I feel like I ordered the wrong thing. I tried my friends birria beef and liked it more than my burrito(burrito was still good tho). A bit pricey but the large portion makes up for it. Would come back again.'}

author: Sasikumar
description: {'en': 'Easily the best Mexican food I‚Äôve had in Singapore ‚Äì authentic flavors, bold seasoning, and well-executed dishes across the board. The only drawback was the seating near the stairs on level two, where there was an unpleasant foot-like odor. Thankfully, the staff were quick to respond and sprayed air freshener to improve the experience.'}

author: chrystelle graciella
description: {'en': 'the portion was huge! the birria beef was so good! free flow tap water. did not try any of their desserts.'}

author: Amanda K
description: {'en': 'food was actly bussin so i und the hype. loaded nachos was yums, fish tacos had a tangy fun mango sauce, the steak quesadillas were p impressive and the steak filling was rly good. queued ard 45 mins on a thursday evening.'}

author: Ïù¥Ìï≠ÎÖï (Andrew Lee)
description: {'en': 'Two of us visited Huevos near Bugis and ended up really enjoying the meal. We ordered the nachos and burritos, and the nachos were especially tasty, crispy and full of flavor. The burrito was filling and had a good mix of ingredients. The food was better than expected, mostly because we went in without high hopes. The place had a relaxed vibe and we paid around 30 per person, which was reasonable for the portion and quality. I would go back if I‚Äôm in the area again.'}

author: ian lee
description: {'en': "The food was really good and definitely worth the price. The birria beef tacos are a must-have but I'd recommend that you get a mix of different tacos if you're dining as a group because any more than 2 of the birria beef is too much."}

author: Ali Jumabhoy
description: {'en': 'Really good Mexican food. Service is great with very friendly staff. In particular enjoyed the calamari.'}

author: Victor Marz
description: {'en': 'Really outstanding and authentic Mexican Tacos. It‚Äòs rare to find such a good Taco in Asia. I have been here several times already and brought many friends who all loved it. My personal favourite is the pulled beef taco. It comes fried from the outside which makes it a wonderfully crispy texture and adds to its taste. While you enjoy your tacos, make sure to try their frozen margarita. Delicious. The service could be better, i.e. we needed to go to the bar to order and re-fill our water a few times and you cannot book a table which often results in extensive wait if you come during peak hours. But still worth it for the food and I will definitely be back many more times.'}

author: rae
description: {'en': "It's my 4th time here! Always have such great hearty meals here. The beef taco is insanely good, you'll want to have more even if you're already full. The place is cozy and everything is kept really clean as well. They don't have many staff so you do have to wait a bit outside even if you have a reservation, worth the wait though."}

author: Jerome Lim
description:
{'en': 'Yeeeeaaaaaaapp

Perfect fix for taco cravings.
Get the beef birra tacos of course. Umami and satisfies all birra desires

The fish taco is spicier than the others but I liked it a lot.

Get the quesadillas, chicken, extra chicken, extra cheese.  This is actually superior to birras in my opinion.

The pico de gallo is a lovely accompaniment to this

Normal chicken tacos are nice. With the avocado which are a nice break. I ate all of this and thoroughly enjoyed it'}

author: Ethan Chua
description: {'en': 'I think food was not bad. Been seeing very good reviews about this place. Not exceptional but good. Waiting time is quite long but it‚Äôs to be expected. Overall pretty solid. Got the chipotle chicken, Baja Fish, Beef as well as the special soft shell crab. I liked the beef best'}

author: Kenny Yap
Jewel Reyes
description: {'en': 'It was a fun night. Food was great. Small space but cozy. We waited like 20mins to be seated and long queue outside if you dont have reservation. Highly recommended for mexican food lovers.'}

author: T L
description:
{'en': 'Please make a reservation at this place! Or you‚Äôd have to queue during peak hours because this place is that popular (deservedly so) üëçüèª

Highly recommend the steak tacos, pork quesadillas and loaded nachos! Steak was tender and juicy, pork was super flavourful.

Got the taquitos this time round cos a friend can‚Äôt take spicy so we were scared and this was good too! The sauce is spicy though so just note if you can‚Äôt spice.

It‚Äôs like my 5th time here - quality has been consistent throughout.'}

author: tan guanyu
description: {'en': 'I don‚Äôt usually leave reviews, but I have to give credit where it‚Äôs due. I visited on a Saturday night and waited about 30 minutes before being seated on level one. To my surprise, there was only one staff member working at the time, handling everything ‚Äî seating guests, taking orders, clearing tables, and even preparing drinks. Despite being on his own, he still managed to provide attentive service. While things were understandably a little slower, I really admired how well he handled the busy crowd. Kudos to him! The food was amazing too, and I‚Äôll definitely be coming back again.'}

author: Kevin Hsieh
Benedict Poh
description: {'en': 'my goto mexican food place. book your appointment in advance and you can avoid the long queue!\n\ngreat food with really big portions and i barely finished half before taking away the rest. very noisy though'}

author: Chloe Lin
description:
{'en': 'Excellent Mexican food!! Best I have had in Singapore. Server is really attentive which we are very appreciative. Atmosphere is cafe style and we like the vibe.

Loved every dishes we ordered (see third picture). Prices are very reasonable.

2 adults, 2 child, we were really full with what we ordered.

I would really recommend this place. And I will definitely be back!!'}

author: Clara Chow
description: {'en': 'Food was really good although it was a little pricey. We had the beef quesadilla which was tender and flavourful, the loaded nachos, some fish tacos and frozen margaritas ü§§went during lunch time without reservations on a weekday. Thankfully didn‚Äôt have to wait long. Would definitely recommend this place for some hearty Mexican food üëç'}

author: Nat N
description: {'en': "Be prepared to queue when coming here. Service is quite slow but the good food makes up for it. I've tried a few Mexican places but Huevos has one of the biggest and most delicious tacos. Very value for money. The portions are bigger compared to other places"}

author: Lim Xin Yi
YQ Lau
description: {'en': 'Ordered nachos, fish tacos and pulled pork quesadillas! The nachos with guacamole was ok. The cheese in the quesadillas was very nice and the fish tacos was very crispy. Do expect a long queue if you come late.'}

author: tomyumdumpling
description: {'en': 'Visited the restaurant during dinner time, the restaurant is located in a cosy area around the Bugis proximity. It is advisable to make a reservation as there was a queue. Although the prices were slightly higher, the food portions were decent. The food is so tasty and filling too! After ordering, the food was served within a short period of time. Definitely a good dining experience to catch-up with friends.'}

author: Marcus Ang
description:
{'en': 'beef tosadas and al pastor pork quesadillas
were phenomenal, proteins were tender and well marinated. loaded nachos was huuuge.
fish tacos were crispy, tangy and not fishy.

portions were huge and sauces pairs well with everything.

do come prepared to wait, even with reservations. but food here is well worth the queue, will definitely come back for more'}

author: Marcus Ho
description:
{'en': 'Nestled in one of the charming heritage shophouses, Huevos offers a cozy, unpretentious dining experience. As I walked in, I was warmly greeted by their youthful staff, who maintained a friendly atmosphere throughout. The restaurant spans two storeys, and after a brief wait, I was seated on the second floor. Despite the afternoon heat, the cold water served at the table was a refreshing touch.

At Huevos, you‚Äôll need to approach the staff to place your order, which adds to the casual vibe. I decided on the Burrito Bowl and Birria Beef Tacos, and I must say, both dishes were a hit. Served hot and packed with flavor, the portions were satisfying and well-priced for the quality.

While the overall ambience is pleasant, I found that the low ceiling on the second floor made conversations from neighbouring tables more noticeable. In my case, a group of four nearby was particularly loud, which slightly dampened the otherwise enjoyable experience. Nonetheless, this is a small quirk of the space rather than a reflection on the restaurant itself.

Huevos is perfect for couples or small groups seeking delicious Mexican food in a quaint setting. I‚Äôll definitely be returning to try more from their menu soon!'}

author: jay k.
description: {'en': 'SO FREAKING GOOD‚Ä¶. every bite was a flavour explosion oh my goodness. a bit on the pricey side but i can say it‚Äôs 100% worth!!! i literally dream of the fish tacos. you might want to go early bc queues form fast after they open!'}

author: G L
description: {'en': 'Great food and cozy atmosphere, quite crowded and walk-in only on weekends! There is a 1 hr dining time limit, so do plan ahead.\n\nDelicious food with decent portions, personal favourites were the mega loaded nachos (huge! $30 for a tray of nachos) fish tacos and quesadillas. Great experience'}

author: sze kin chan
description: {'en': 'generous protion of food. Taco was very flavorful, but a bit too oily.'}

author: Janelle C
Cheryl
description: {'en': 'Best mexican food in town! Waited for about an hour even tho we were early for dinner at 530pm, but it was well worth the wait. For starters, we recommended the onion petals, which had a good crumb and came with a delicious dip. The other mains were all delicious, especially the quesadillas, which came with lots of cheese! Mega loaded nachos was good for 8 of us to share with all of us getting mains to go with.'}
owner_responses: {'en': {'text': 'Thank you for the kinds words\n Cheryl , love you ü•∞üòò ‚Ä¶'}}

author: Oh XX
description: {'en': 'Partner and I enjoyed this soooo much.\nThe best Mexican food we tried thus far. Highly recommend the loaded nachos and pork quesadillas! Just come and try really'}

author: Steveo 88
description: {'en': 'Probably the best Mexican food I had in Singapore. My group of friends and I (8 people in total) queued for about 1 hour and 15 minutes for a table.\n\nThe vibrant and flavorful food, including tacos, enchiladas, and guacamole, featured fresh ingredients and a perfect balance of spices. The ambiance is lively and welcoming.'}

author: Natasha Tjahjadi
description: {'en': 'Luckily came with a big group so we could try loads of things: birria quesadilla/ taco, al pastor quesadilla/ taco, baja taco and gambas taco, corn cob and loaded nachos. Best things were corn cob (was really better than expected, slightly charred, spiced up and cheese) and the birria taco!\n\nWill dream of this until the next time I get to eat it. Come early because the queue gets really long. They are really strict with the dining hours because of the queue.'}

author: Shan Khoo
description: {'en': 'Went to both outlets and food is always on point! Repeated orders were their loaded nachos. The chicken used was so tender, not dry at all, guac was fresh, and it was a mountain enough for 2 pax! Queues are just really long so I hope for more outlets!!'}

author: John Lee
description: {'en': 'Waited for 1.5 hours. But the food and service was worth the wait. Probably the best Mexican food I‚Äôve tried in Singapore. Yes the food is pricy but the portions make up for it imo. The service was excellent, despite it being crowded they still paid attention to each of the customers needs and queries. Try the Cauliflower bites, Birria tacos, Birria Quesadilla and the mega loaded nachos those 3 items should feed 3/4 people comfortably. 5/5 fire emojis thanks Heidi and the other lady for taking care of us tonight. W service no cap.'}

author: Yuchen L
Howard
description: {'en': 'Small location but there aren\'t too many Mexican options around Singapore, so this gets extra points for that. Plus the staff were just super nice - laid back but still attentive and kind. The tacos were fantastic: they pack a punch (the waiter wasn\'t kidding when he checked "you\'re ok with spice, right?") but they were delicious. It\'s not exactly cheap - 2x tacos were $14 and 3x for $18 but it felt worth it.'}

author: Jerlyn Ackerman
description:
{'en': "The only place you must go regardless how far the restaurant isü•π Whether you are a tourist or local, this place is seriously so good, I'm considering coming back for anniversary date special mealü•π

Huevos is a mexican restaurant slightly out of nowhere between lavender mrt and bugis mrt and near Hotel Boss, it requires a bit of walking but for the food, I would say it's so worth it‚ù§Ô∏è

My partner and I showed up without a reservation because despite the good reviews, it was a weekday and we believed that we would be able to get a seat. Didn't expect them to be full-house despite the 1 hour dining time restriction (not very strict but of course don't test your luck haha), but we got our seats really quickly! The crew was so friendly and professional, they explain the layout and you just know what to do, where to order and stuff. The food came and everything was way beyond our expectations, loaded nachos is the best I had in Singapore, the tortillas was so thin and crispy like you never had and it was so packed with toppings and the tangy sour from the lime ‚ù§Ô∏è the tacos are absolutely gorgeous and packed full of flavour, it's like the one thing you crave and you will definitely get satisfied! The al pastor pork tacos was amazing and the hard shell taco was perfection(Legit), you have to make sure you get the right tacos, one soft shell and one hard shell to try everything out! Drinks was unique, we had a cinnamon rice milk and a salt chilli rimmed glass of passion fruit slushie, Huevos just screams authentic and flavourfulü•π

We only ordered the tacos and the nachos this time but I don't think you can go wrong ordering anything here. Just remember to queue at the door and wait, they will come and greet you~

In order for you to really try the food, we recommend bringing a friend as the nachos is quite big for the smallest size and you just have to get the nachos too!

Just take note of their closing time too, they have a store closed at noon so we had our last order taken at 2pm!"}

author: mame goma
description: {'en': 'The portions were decent. most things on the menu are delicious, but fish tacos were a let down, and tasted similar to filet o fish from mcdonalds.'}

author: Keiko Shan
description: {'en': 'Have to do booking else will be a long Q. No reservations in Friday night.'}

author: R L
description: {'en': 'Loved the food so much! Taco is my favourite and the quesadillas is a must-try too. All of my family went off with over-full stomach.\nIt is very popular now in Singapore, and it is highly recommended to come early for the queue.'}

author: Josephine Tan
description: {'en': 'Often a long queue to get in, but it‚Äôs worth the wait. (More sitting area upstairs ‚Ä¶) Authentic taste, delightful, and generous portions, perfect for sharing. The friendly service staff added to the overall experience. Will be back üòä'}

author: Lee Zhi Peng
description: {'en': "Have visited multiple times, never fails to deliver. Be prepared for long queues on Friday/weekend nights though.\n\nOnce upon a time I had their beef tongue quesadilla? Was told it was seasonal. Please bring it back it was amazing :')"}

author: GY
description: {'en': 'Delicious, with huge portions. Would recommend getting the loaded nachos, the baja fish tacos as well as the pulled pork quesadillas.\n\nCome earlier if you want to avoid queuing especially on the weekends'}

author: Elvis Tan
description: {'en': 'Came here for dinner on a wed night and arrived about 7pm and theres was already a queue formed up, not a long one yet. Waited about 15mins to get in and we ordered the tacos, quesadillas and nachos and everything was amazing and so worth it for its price! The beef birria quesadillas tasted so good with a mixtures of spices and herbs thats makes it so flavourful, along with the birria sauce. Got the fish taco and the fish was so fresh, however the jam on it wasn‚Äôt for me personally but you can still try it! The mega loaded nachos was the most worth it dish to get tho! Such a huge portion and they were so generous with the fillings! Looking forward to my next visit'}

author: Pamela Aw Yong
description: {'en': "Reservations only available on Tues/Wed/Thurs. Other days are walk-in only. Highly recommended to make a reservation if possible as the queues get long. Birria tacos are awesome, pork tacos also good. Skip on the chicken tacos.\n\nCeviche is a must-order, very refreshing but you'll have to get some chips on the side otherwise it's strange eating it on it's own. Their tortilla chips are a little too thin and didn't have the toasty corn flavour so that was a pity. All in all still delicious, would come again!"}

author: MC Chow
description: {'en': 'Tasty food and good vibe. However if you haven‚Äôt booked in advance, you might expect almost 30 mins to 1 hour of queuing.\n\nAlso, no credit card is accepted.'}

author: Ang Wei Lin
description:
{'en': 'The food was really good, we got their loaded nachos and tacos.

Even though we had a reservation, they were really packed and the staff was really busy so we had to wait quite a while. They also accidentally gave another table our tacos and we had to wait for an additional 20 mins after finishing the nachos.

Would definitely recommend making a reservation before going though, I went on a Monday afternoon and it was packed.

I would highly recommend going for the food though, it was amazing!!'}

author: Megan Ng
description:
{'en': 'The best Mexican restaurant I‚Äôve ever been to so far. Every dishes here are amazing, tasty and fresh. My favorite is fish tacos which comes with hot and crispy baja piece, mixed well with the sauce. Quesadilla was filled with lots of mushroom and cheese. Not really interested in the loaded nachos but it came with a huge portion. Every dish was served hot. We have to get the horchata (strong sense of cinnamon) and agua fresca (so fresh with watermelon juice and mint leaves) every time.
The staffs are super friendly and helpful.
Would be long queue during peak hour but they will open second floor so the queue will move quite fast. The place might be a bit noisy sometimes due to the soundproofing.
This is the place that I will remain coming back for sure. Affordable price with delicious food!!'}

author: Jeffrey Ng
description:
{'en': "Probably the best I have had in Singapore, came here on a weekday exactly at 5PM and there was people already queuing up.

I must say the fish tacos were well-made, though it looks a bit burnt on the batter.

The pulled-pork quesadillas was amazing with the thick amount of cheese they had inside.

The loaded nachos was the most worth it dish to get ! Such a huge portion and they were so generous with the fillings!

Don't remember the name of the drink but it was great too!

Looking forward to my next visit!"}

author: Hanni Koh
description:
{'en': 'Definitely the best Mexican restaurant in Singapore. The food here has been consistently great and affordable over the past couple of years. I‚Äôm super proud to take my friends here because Huevos never disappoints!

I highly recommend their quesadillas and their loaded nachos. Extremely flavourful stuff that‚Äôs also great for sharing. I am also a massive fan of their house made Horchattaü•õ, which is perfectly sweet and smooth. It‚Äôs an awesome beverage to kill the spice. If you enjoy an alcoholic beverage, I‚Äôd also recommend their frozen margarita. It‚Äôs the perfect slushy texture, and they are definitely not skimping on the alcohol.

If you can handle spice, make sure you try their homemade chilli sauce as well. üå∂Ô∏è

Despite the small team, the service here has always been great. The staff are friendly and will help you if you need recommendations. however, since it is a very popular spot, expect some waiting time during peak hour. It‚Äôs best to make a reservation online if you can as the restaurant is small.'}

author: Peirson
description: {'en': "Awesome Tacos, warm receptive service, nice, cooling and doesn't feel packed for a busy service.\n\nbut indie rock in a mexican restaurant üôÇ\u200d‚ÜîÔ∏è"}

author: Skye Cai
description:
{'en': 'Had the amazing Mexican dishes here.
The fried fish tacos is one of the best. Fish filet deep fried and covered with a thin layer of crispy skin, it was served still hot, so it‚Äôs amazing.
The sauce of top is a little spicy with the mango dices, it gets a little sweet. Such an amazing combination.
The nachos is freshly baked with cheese and  fresh avocado.
Fresh churros are good, soft and crispy. Great chocolate sauce.'}

author: randall
description: {'en': "Very nice Mexican food! Just that the place is kinda tiny so you should reserve or go early to queue. Definitely recommend the fish tacos and loaded nachos. Maybe the only complaint is the slow service for how small the place is. Food takes a while even if you're first into the shop. Kitchen staff must be swamed\n\nOverall a great place and im already planning to go back again."}

author: JY
description: {'en': 'This restaurant serves the best Mexican food in Sg. Every dish that we ordered was delicious. The onion petals was suprisingly good- think of it as a lighter version of onion rings, but it petal form. The signature baja fish tacos and pork quesadillas were delicious as well, while the loaded nachos were chock full of Ingredients. What was the best was how valid for money it was. It was $80+ for 4 dishes; which is a steal compared to other Mexican restaurants.\n\nHowever, do note that there is a strict 1 hour turn around for tables, and they only allow entry when the entire table has arrived.'}

author: Dan Stryker
description: {'en': "I highly recommend this Mexican restaurant's delectable Chipotle Chicken quesadilla! The meat filling is savory, moist and soft. Well worth $16! We also tried the crispy Baja fish, it was spicier than expected. The loaded nachos dish has   generous servings of avocados along with meat and of course...nachos. Can't wait to come again"}

author: New Ghost
description: {'en': 'My go to place for Mexican! Loaded Nachos, Quesadilla with chipotle chicken, cheese & jalape√±os, yums!!! The baja fish tacos is a must-order too! üòò\nPayment is Nets or *i think* fave pay, perhaps can explore paywave (visa, Mastercard etc) now that you‚Äôve adjusted your menu pricing? üôèü§ù\nEnded our meal with some nice caramel Churros, just perfecto! ü§ôüëç'}

author: Himanshu Gupta
description: {'en': 'Nice authentic Mexican üá≤üáΩfood you can get . Great atmosphere, plenty of place to accommodate many guests at level one & level two. Smiling staff with good service & plenty of dishes to choose from .\nGreat place to dine in with family & or friends . ‚Ä¶'}

author: Digital Foodprint
description:
{'en': 'One of the best spot for Mexican food so far! Be sure to make your reservation ahead of time as this place will be packed during peak hours.

We‚Äôve ordered the following for a group of 5:
- Mega Loaded Nachos
- Al Pastor Pork and Birria Beef Quesadillas
- Baja Fish Tacos

The quesadillas were stuffed generously, fish taco came with a close to palm sized breaded fish and the nachos were piled up like a mountain. Taste of all these items easily exceeded any Mexican restaurant out there. Definitely come in a group as you want to try more variations!'}

author: Nick Lim
description: {'en': 'Great place for delicious Mexican food. However, you need to be patient‚Ä¶ just have to queue on weekend because can‚Äôt make reservation.'}

author: Jacky Wu
description: {'en': "This has got to be the best Mexican food I've eaten till date! Awesome tacos and quesadillas. Best favourite is the fried fish! Highly highly recommended! Place is small so seats are quite limited."}

author: Darren Lee
description:
{'en': "Just had dinner at Huevos for the fifth or sixth time, and once again, the quality and quantity were consistently excellent.

I started with my go-to, the Rancheros. I‚Äôve always preferred this over the loaded nachos as it's more satisfying and flavorful. The combination of beef, guacamole, salsa, egg, black beans, and pickled onions pairs perfectly with the nacho chips.

I also ordered my favorites: the trinity mushroom and birria beef quesadillas. They never fail to amaze me. The quesadilla shell was crispy, with juicy meat and mushrooms inside, all topped with flavorful sauces.

Today, I tried two new items. The first was the barbacoa lamb taco. I typically go for the Baja fish taco, but the lamb might replace it as my go-to. The lamb was meaty yet not overpowering, with a nice kick of spice. I also tried their frozen margarita, which was fantastic and will be a must-have moving forward. The flavors blended smoothly with the tequila, making it very refreshing. Sipping it while enjoying the mains really elevated the whole gastronomic experience.

However, do note that weekday dinners and weekends can see long queues, and all members of your party must be present before being seated. The food preparation time can be a bit lengthy, but it‚Äôs worth the wait.

Arguably the best Mexican food in Singapore, I would highly recommend."}
owner_responses: {'en': {'text': 'Love u'}}

author: Yihui
description: {'en': 'One of the best Mexican places in Singapore. Generous portions and good value for money. Recommend the Baja Nuggies and Baja Fish Tacos!'}

author: Daniel Wong
description:
{'en': "Great little Mexican joint. Not the best I've eaten but some items are definitely must tries. The best dish was the Birria Torta. The beef was tender and full of beefy flavour. In fact order anything with Birria Beef and it will be good.
We tried 3 types of tacos but only the lamb impressed us. The carne asada (beef) although cooked medium rare was lacking in flavour and the fish was on the dry side.
The loaded nachos is a great for sharing. The Al Pastor Quesadilla was the only pork item we ordered but it's just OK, would've been better if the filling was the Birria or Barbacoa lamb.
It's a small place so go early to avoid the queues even on weekdays. Prices are reasonable and best of all, no GST!"}

author: Roy Yong
description: {'en': 'Nice but be careful of queues on weekends, and to make reservations via email or phone for large groups. Loaded nachos are a must.'}

author: Jesslyne Lee
description: {'en': 'Tacos were really loaded, fresh and flavourful. Servings were all generous. A definite recommend!!'}

author: Andy Yeo
description: {'en': 'The food was great because I think we over ordered and my sons loved overeating Mexican stuff üòÖü§¶\u200d‚ôÇÔ∏èüò¨\n\nI like how authentic was the taste and how it is rustic like how it‚Äôs actually eaten. But seriously? I was won over by their free flow sauces. üòÇ'}

author: Ryan Ng
description:
{'en': 'Was greeted with a warm smile at the door and shown to my seat‚Äîreally set a nice tone for the evening. I arrived around 5:45 PM and the place was already packed, full of energy and good vibes all around.

There was a bit of a wait for the food, but honestly, it was well worth it. Every dish was super flavourful and clearly made with a lot of care. Can tell the kitchen takes pride in what they do. Already looking forward to coming back to try more.

Shoutout to the service team too‚Äîthey were friendly, attentive, and made sure everything went smoothly for us.

Well done, Huevos! Definitely lives up to the hype.'}
owner_responses: {'en': {'text': 'Hello Ryan,\n\nThank you thank you for leaving us this review! Glad everything went smoothly and you enjoyed your time with us :)'}}

author: Tian
description: {'en': 'Loaded nachos were very yummy! Tacos were good too'}

author: C
description:
{'en': 'Quality Mexican food at affordable price. Would recommend going earlier or making reservations to avoid long queues.

Must try: Baja Fish Taco!
What we ordered: Four tacos, one quesadilla, and nacho.
Number of diner: Two
Damage: S$55
Verdict: worth traveling down for the food. It‚Äôs good and filling'}

author: H L
description:
{'en': 'Had to queue a while on a Friday evening but queue seemed to move quicker than I expected. Ordered:

Trinity Mushroom Quesadilla - $16
Not a fan of mushroom, personal preference but came with plenty of cheese

Al Pastor Quesadilla - $16
I loved it!! Recommended ‚≠êÔ∏è

4) Loaded Nachos - $20
Portion was huge! Love the guacamole. Came with plenty of toppings (meat, cheese‚Ä¶) Recommended ‚≠êÔ∏è

The staff was also really kind to let us know that the portions are huge and not to order one quesadilla each. For three pax, this was also a little difficult to finish, had to pack 2 pieces of quesadilla.'}

author: Nainika Agrawal
Zixuan Wang (Amber)
description: {'en': 'Best Mexican in Singapore no doubt. The beef taco is definitely the best one for me. The Baja fish taco we didn‚Äôt take a photo of it, it‚Äôs good tho, the fish is fried crispy but a bit different from what we expected from Baja fish.\nOverall this place really good, food in generous portion, price is decent for Mexican food in Singapore too.\nWe over ordered and barely finished what we ordered, the bill was around 45 per person. Have service charge but No GST.'}

author: Xian Xuan
description: {'en': 'This is my second time back and it is definitely still up to standards. I came back because my friend and I were craving their loaded nachos and it didn‚Äôt disappoint. All their other dishes are really good too, super flavourful and filling. The only thing is that the place gets quite crowded and cleanliness couldn‚Äôt be kept up to standard therefore it felt slightly uncomfortable. But nothing too much of a bother and I absolutely love their food so I‚Äôll definitely be back again.'}

author: JATHL
description: {'en': 'Excellent Mexican food! I ordered the lengua quesadillas and they were so good I had to try more, so I had the fish tacos as well! Awesome meal! Frozen margarita was good too!\nHad a chat with their team and found them very passionate and knowledgeable!\nI will definitely return to try the Birria! üëçüëçüëå'}

author: Maximilian
description: {'en': 'Great casual Mexican restaurant. Tacos are flavorful and tasty, good variety of starters to select from. Margaritas are great as well. Expect some queue and waiting time during peak hours. Would just wish that the New Bahru outlet also had the chicken tacos..'}

author: Zenos Jake
description:
{'en': 'IMHO Huevos is one of the best Mexican restaurants in Singapore.

I‚Äôve ordered take out from them several times and haven‚Äôt had a single bad dish. Despite tacos and tortillas not traveling very well in general, their food is always delicious. This is the first time I‚Äôve eaten at their restaurant and their food is even better in person!

After living in Mexico for a year I regularly crave Mexican style street corn, and it is absolutely scrumptious from Huevos. If you‚Äôve never tried it please give it a go!

Beyond that, my favourite dishes are their quesadillas, baja fish tacos, and beef tacos (don‚Äôt forget to dip these in the sauce!)

I‚Äôm so full and already can‚Äôt wait to eat here again üòÇ'}
owner_responses:
{'en': {'text': "Hola Zenos!

Thank you for your bussin review!
It's always a pleasure when we finally get to meet our friends from behind the delivery screens! <3
We‚Äôre glad to hear that you enjoyed dining with us at Huevos.
Our team always strives to provide a great dining experience for our guests, and we‚Äôll be sure to pass on your compliments to our teams as reviews like yours always makes our day.

It's always great to see a familiar face! We will always welcome you again at Huevos!

Warmest Regards,
Huevos"}}

author: littlebitofnoms
description:
{'en': 'VERY WORTH IT. Great food, great portions, at a very reasonable price.
MUST get the loaded nachos here. That alone is enough for me!!!

What we tried:
ü§§ Baja Fish Tacos (10/10)
This is the most popular item on the menu, and rightfully so. Generous servings of fish, and the fish was hot and crispy, savoury and meat tender. Really like the fish! Mango salsa  was a great match, completing the taco. These fish tacos were a delicious mix of sour, sweet, spicy and savoury. If you love fish and strong flavours, you would love this! üåÆüëå

ü§§ Loaded Nachos (11/10)
Very worth it, great for sharing. Didn‚Äôt even get a photo of it, was too excited to dive in. Has so many ingredients, refreshing, and SO GOOD. Will come back for this!!! Love the mix of guac, pico de gallo, meat, cheese, nachos‚Ä¶ ü§§üòãüòãüòãcan share between 2-3 people.
Please try this!! (Imo i like it more than the fish tacos)

ü§§ Kids Quesadilla Jr
A serving of 4 quesadillas filled with cheese, bacon, corn.. all the things kids will love. Quite huge, can share with 2 kids!

We came on Saturday at 1pm, queued for about 25-30 mins, food arrived after 10~ mins. Would recommend coming on weekdays with reservation, but I would say it was worth the wait, the food was so satisfying!!! ‚ù§Ô∏è Had a great lunch, will be back! HIGHLY RECOMMEND. üëçüèª'}

author: wendy
description: {'en': 'Finally had a chance to try! Went on a Thursday evening at 630pm and the queue was not too long. The loaded nachos is definitely a must-try! Each bite was a burst of flavours, sweet spicy tangy. The beef in the beef taco was succulent too! Habanero wings were a tad too spicy tho, overshadowing the flavours of the other dishes. But will definitely revisit!'}

author: Victoria Wong
description: {'en': 'I‚Äôve sampled quite a few Mexican places in SG and I must say that huevos rly delivers in terms of flavours and affordability. Our absolute favs are the baja tacos & loaded nachos (the guac is aceüëåüèª)!\n\nThe space is quite cosy, so I‚Äôd suggest dropping by just before or after peak hours to avoid having to wait (they unfortunately don‚Äôt accept reservations on weekends). Props to the service crew who‚Äôve been incredibly warm & friendly!'}

author: Alicia Tan
Audrey Nmy
description: {'en': "Ordered the birria, burrito bowl and margarita. Place was a little small with limited seating so do come earlier. This was really delicious, all the ingredients are fresh too. The portions are generous, you'll definitely be full :)"}

author: Kenneth Lee
description: {'en': 'No frills restaurant with solid quality items. The loaded nachos are great, and I must say the fish tacos were well-made. Carnitas were also juicy and flavourful.'}

author: BeholdHim
description: {'en': 'So thankful that a friend recommended me this place. It was so good and we thoroughly enjoyed every dish and beverage we had. There is a limited time duration at dinner due to limited eating. Do go upstairs for a more spacious setting. The ladies servers were patient and firstly. Always willing to answer our questions. Beef and fish were great. Will definitely be back again!'}

author: Rajeevan Neeraj
description: {'en': 'Great Mexican restaurant and vibe is awesome! Not too heavy on the wallet.'}

author: Kenrick Widjaja
description:
{'en': "Great little taco place. Prepare to queue though.
Price is cheaper compared to other taco joints. But taste and quality are excellent. Nachos was crispy and thin. The quesadillas was meaty. And tacos was simply the best.
There was a dipping sauce which enhanced everything you dipped into.
Must try all the salsa, you can ask for milk if it gets too spicy.

The cocktail was interesting, red & sweet at first, but after a while it got brown and stronger... In overall I'll definitely will come again and will try different menu."}

author: Srihari Raghavan
description:
{'en': 'Lunch with my daughter based on her friends recommendation.

The place was quite busy on a late Sunday afternoon. There was waiting, but we got a table for 2 almost immediately. That was nice‚Ä¶ w we had heard that when‚Äôs have long wait times üòÖ

The food was delicious‚Ä¶. The service was efficient‚Ä¶ the decor was quite basic and the Aircon was not really working!! But who cares the food hot so the right spots!!

Would definitely be back here‚Ä¶ soon!'}

author: Zhikun Soh
description:
{'en': 'Note:
1. Fri and Weekends are strictly walk-in.
2. Be early before 6PM, queues get longer after 6PM.
3. You queue outside, while the staff will occasionally go out to bring people in whenever the tables are available. So make sure everyone is here before that. You can only go in after everyone has all arrived.
4. 1 hour dining limit

Want to go back and try other dishes. The food is really awesome, as like what the other reviews have rightfully pointed out.'}

author: jordan chong
description:
{'en': 'Geez the staff is quite unfriendly but god damn the food is good.

But acutally the staff is not that bad... we said we only had 3 poeple but we had someone else join us after and he still let the person come in so at the end of the day i think he is a nice guy.

He also tell us that the chilli was spicy and gees it was fricking fricking spicy so that was that thanks brother

The queue is insane but the food is insane as well so i think it is warranted.... book early so you dont have to queue and make sure you arrive on time cos they give your seat away after 15 mins'}

author: Jason Sentell
description: {'en': 'Awesome spot. We tried the fish tacos, birria tacos & the nachos. Hard to pick a winner btw the three, they were all stand-outs. It was a busy lunch crowd on a Sunday but service was friendly and attentive. We will certainly be coming back to try more of the menu items and the margaritas. Price is good value for money.'}

author: Jasper Ting
description: {'en': "Recommended by a friend to try and wasn't disappointed. Had the loaded fries, birria beef quesadilla, and pork carnitas tacos. The nachos was a good starter filled with ingredients and even had meat as the base. The pork carnitas was juicy and full of flavor. The beef quesadilla was cheesy.\n\n10/10 will come back again. Have to come early for dinner cause there was a queue when we left at 7pm."}

author: Emman K
description: {'en': 'Excellent and quality food, with selections being very value-for-money. Staff are attentive and courteous. The atmosphere is great, but the seating is a little cramped. Try to avoid going in groups of more than 6-7. Overall, an excellent experience, will gladly come again!'}

author: XingDe Chen
description: {'en': 'My wife and I had a lovely meal. Best Mexican food we‚Äôve tasted. Scallop Ceviche was amazing. Loaded Nachos was really ‚Äòloaded.‚Äô Birria Beef & Baja Fish were yummilicious. Shaken margarita was simply delightful. Will definitely bring family and friends.'}

author: Lim Yi Ying
description: {'en': 'Friendly staff, always happy to help and polite even though place is busy! Food is amazing, spice lovers will definitely enjoy the homemade ghost pepper sauceü•∞ slushie flavours are seasonal and hasnt missed any marks for me the last 4 visits I‚Äôve been there. Recommend to make a reservation before heading down, and bring friends along to try more variety of food!'}

author: David Vincent Daniel
description: {'en': 'Been to Huevos many times but never got to writing a review. Not because there is nothing to tell but it‚Äôs because I‚Äôm always overloaded and blown away by the food. These guys kept the menu simple and  the taste consistent. I am never disappointed when I visit. My must try is the Lamb Tacos.'}
owner_responses: {'en': {'text': 'You are the G.'}}

author: penny
J
description: {'en': 'This place does very good Mexican food! The loaded nachos and quesadilla are my favourites - so much flavour in each bite! Tacos are quite good as well, would recommend getting the Baja fish though it was abit too spicy! Will definitely be back!'}
owner_responses: {'en': {'text': 'Love u jo'}}

author: Jeslin Lavigne
description: {'en': "One of the Best mexican food I ever tried. Especially the Loaded Nachos, it's a must to order it because its not simply just nachos.. the sauces they use, the meat in it is real good. Beef tacos is good. Especially the dipping sauce. And not to forget their Lvl 1 to 4 spicy sauces on each table. Affordable price range. Good services from staff. Thumbs up!!"}

author: Janelle N.
description: {'en': 'no1 mexican place in singapore & always will be <3 the consistency of food over the years, we love huevos too much that words could ever describe. from tortilla chips, guac, ceviche, pork burrito bowl, baha taco! margarita everything is just so so good!'}

author: Jamie
description: {'en': 'First time eating here after seeing all the reviews and all I gotta say is: the food is soooo good and in my books, the best Mexican restaurant in Singapore!\n\nStaff was really nice too when they saw my little one struggling with the heat as she accidentally ate one of the spiciest sauce. I‚Äôll be back for sure to try the rest of the menu!'}

author: D R Taylor
description:
{'en': 'Ordered nachos, fish tacos üåÆand quesadilla. They were all so yummy. ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê

Especially with the different sauce. I was so excited to try all the sauces. My favorite sauce would be Valentina Salsa Picanto; a good mix of sour, salty, a tiny hint of sweet n just the right amount of spicy. A few drops of the spiciest sauce of them all made me cried involuntarily for a whole 5min. I was thankful of the lime drink recommended. ü•∫üòÖ

Love the nachos! There were pickled onion petals, diced tomatoes, herbs, jalapenos, my all-time favorite mashed guacamole all bound together with warm melted cheese. Just heaven. üòç

Fish tacos was nice. Big chunks of fish and deep fried to perfection. Great texture. I had wished it was a little more savoury. üòÑ

I am definitely going back.'}

author: JK Chow (Jingzyy)
description: {'en': "An awesome place to enjoy great Mexican food at a decent price. Can't really comment on authenticity, but you can't go wrong with layers of melted cheese, onions and guacamole blanketing crispy nacho chips. I recommend the quesidilla and loaded nachos.\n\nOnly gripe is the suuuper long queue in the hot outdoors. I would say it's worth to try once, then decide if you ever want to queue again!"}

author: Darius Guo
description:
{'en': 'Definitely the best Mexican gastronomic experience you can find in Singapore.

We ordered the guacamole salsa with doritoes, ceviche, mushroom quesadillas, fish tacos and had drinks alongside.

The quesadillas were out of this world as it was a very delicious blend of cheese and mushrooms with the great burst of earthy flavours.

Fish tacos were nuts too as the crispiness of the fish gives a nice balance to the taco.

Only issue I have though minor is the seating of the area as the place is small and air conditioning is warm.

Other than that highly recommend Huevos to all Mexican lovers!'}

author: mark . m
description: {'en': "my wife regarded this as the best Mexican food in town. I can't agree more - we can really sit there and eat all day long, but we know we can't hoard the seat because it's a relatively small space. prices are generally wallet-friendly but we all know Mexican food is never really cheap in Singapore, which is quite an irony, since many of them are street food. Nice interior with cool mural. waiting period for food is tolerable despite high volume delivery orders and full house. sauces are too spicy to my liking, but the taste is authentic. am clueless about the food name but the fish in the wrap, that's a bomb, even for non-seafood persons like my wife. the Mexican drinks are surprisingly affordable unlike many other restaurants - the co-owner told us they want more people to try and love Mexican food for awareness - brilliant. perhaps the only problem is the difficulty in looking for car park nearby but well worth the hassle!"}

author: Denise T
description: {'en': 'Great food here but the queue situation wasn‚Äôt handled very well. It‚Äôll be good to give us online queue numbers. Waitress wasn‚Äôt very friendly.'}
owner_responses:
{'en': {'text': 'Hey Denise!
Terribly sorry to hear that.
Could I trouble you to let me know more about what happened at 84844825?
Would love to understand better to enhance the future experience!
Looking forward to hearing from you!'}}

author: Yan Rong Tan
description: {'en': "the food was solid, but the wait was a bit long around 30mins. there's also a long queue, so better to book a reservation beforehand :) i sat at the balcony when i dined there, good atmosphere and music. highly recommend the loaded nachos for sharing, fish tacos and al pastor quesidilla. great mexican food"}
owner_responses: {'en': {'text': 'Love you'}}

author: Amelia Lee
description:
{'en': "AMAZING FOODDD

We had Fish tacos, Al pastor pork Quesadilla and loaded nachos and it adds up to $16.90 per pax for 3 of us.

Fish tacos- didn't know the fish was fried but it doesn't feel oily and the fish was huge so it really fills with every bite. Really worth it.

Loaded nachos- usually not a fan of nachos but this really doesn't taste like regular nachos, I love the guac in it.

Al Pastor Pork- One of my personal fave, really flavourful and the cheese in it is really ooofff

overall 5/5!"}

author: Ben C
description: {'en': 'Awesome food and great portions but try to avoid peak hours if possible.'}

author: enoch k
description: {'en': 'Food was amazing!! Highly recommend the Loaded Nachos, Chipotle Chicken Quesadilla and Baja Fish Tacos, especially the last one. The portion was huge and we ended up having to takeaway our leftovers. Price was super reasonable and the food was worth every penny. Service was great and staff was really helpful. The only thing is you have to make a reservation as the queue is quite long. Eating time is limited to one hour, but since the service is really fast, that‚Äôs okay too. This might be my new favourite restaurant!'}

author: ananya shukla
description: {'en': 'Nice cozy place, food is really nice. Service is also good. Must try if you like Mexican food'}

author: tara lim
description: {'en': 'Absolutely loved the loaded nachos and beef quesadilla! Will definitely be back. Everything was tender, saucy and just so delicious yums. Also for the loaded nachos might want to share with 3-4 pax. I got the outdoor seating and was bitten by mozzies so minus 1 point for atmosphere'}

author: hope
description: {'en': 'Birria beef tacos were really good. Had to wait for about an hour for seats on a weekend evening.'}

author: Amy Lee
description: {'en': "Best quesadillas I've had in SG, nachos were solid too. Service was a bit slow/inefficient but I think that was because they were understaffed that day, so no big deal. Hope to return again to satisfy Mexican food cravings!"}

author: Trotting Horse
description:
{'en': 'Be prepared to queue if you are here during peak hours. We queued for almost an hour before we got a table on a Sat evening for dinner. Not easy to spot the entrance but can see the queue from a far. üòä
The Baja Fish Tacos is very good with the mango salsa and crispy fried fish. This left the deepest impression. Unique but very tasty. The mushroom quesadilla is great too. Love the generous portion of mushrooms, perfect for mushrooms lovers like me. The cheese is also the right amount.
The churros are ok. The better ones in Singapore but I thought if the batter is lighter, would have been better.

Tip: somehow mobile coverage doesn‚Äôt quite work inside the cafe. This explains why they provide wifi password once we seated. Plus points for thoughtfulness. ‚ù§Ô∏è so use the wifi to read the menu.  üòä

Would come back again but will try to avoid peak hour queue. üòÖ

P.S. we sat right across the payment counter and that corner is rather stuffy as the aircon doesn‚Äôt reach there. That‚Äôs the only downside but we wanted a table quick in a small cafe with long line. I think a ventilator fan might help with circulation of air.'}

author: Kendrick Wee
description: {'en': 'Excellent Mexican food. Very reasonable price and friendly service. The nachos were really good. Big serving size as well. Outdoor seatings were available was well.'}

author: Amos Tong
description: {'en': 'This place is absolutely 5 stars and currently the best Mex in sg !\nSometimes there is a queue outside but it moves very quickly . I strongly recommend the fish tacos , the corn , lamb taco and cerviche. Love the hot sauce too üî•'}

author: Rachel Ho
description:
{'en': 'came in a group of 6 which was great as we got to try many different flavours of tacos and quesadillas.

my fav was the fish tacos, were which crispy outside and soft insides. üêüüåÆ
the loaded nachos were also a standout with its delicious flavour and huge portions! very worth it!

prices are also reasonable in an expensive place like singapore, so i think it‚Äôs a good place to go for a catch up with friends üòã'}

author: Natalie
description: {'en': 'kinda expensive but portions are GENEROUS so overall quite worth the money! delicious mexican food, probably the best i‚Äôve had so far. do note that you have to make a reservation (up to 1 month in advance) as this place is very popular‚Äî and i can see why!'}

author: Lorenzo Y.
description: {'en': "Huevos is unassumingly good. I really appreciate the level of service rendered by the young gentleman soloing the counter. It's so refreshing to be served cold water upon your arrival. And to be provided napkins soon after. The gentleman even recommended the respective sauces for our food according to our aversion for spicy food. His attention to detail is impecible. Food wise, we tried the nachos, cauliflower burrito bowl, fish tacos and cheese quesadilla. Overall, the food was great. Price and portion was reasonable. No complaints at all. I saw other reviews mentioning that the pricing wasn't good. I've eaten at other Mexican restaurants that were more expensive but tasted bad. I would definitely come back and patronise Huevos again. Limited seating and they only accept walk in on weekends. To avoid disappointment, arrive early or during non peak hours if possible."}

author: redcrumb
description: {'en': 'Very interesting flavours! Tacos are bursting with flavours, acidity and good level of spice. The taco meat and pork belly is a little dry. Fried onion has quite a nice flavour! Chocolate sauce is pretty interesting but feels like can be improved alittle more. Definitely worth visiting! Will be back to try other stuff!'}
owner_responses:
{'en': {'text': "Hola Ray!

Thank you for your lovely review!

We‚Äôre glad to hear that you enjoyed dining with us at Huevos.
Our team always strives to provide a great dining experience for our guests, and we‚Äôll be sure to pass on your compliments to our teams as reviews like yours always makes our day.

Thank you for your kind words and constructive feedback! We will do our best and improve on serving you better.

It's always great to see a familiar face! We look forward to welcoming you again soon!

Warmest Regards,
Huevos"}}

author: _r
description: {'en': 'The Birria Beef tacos are outstanding- the best Mexican I have had in Singapore. It‚Äôs a small place, likely need to queue for a few minutes, but we‚Äôll worth it. The staff was very friendly, service great‚Ä¶I‚Äôll be back for sure.'}

author: Bevlyn Tan
description: {'en': 'I would say hands down one of the top fuss free Mexican places in Singaporeüòç It‚Äôs really affordable but they definitely do not skimp on the flavour! Must gets are definitely the nachos and baja fish tacosü§§! ‚Ä¶'}
owner_responses: {'en': {'text': 'Flavour town babyyyyy'}}

author: SunCheom Jin
description:
{'en': "As this restaurant doesn't accept reservations, it's ideal to avoid peak hours especially in the afternoon as you will have to wait outside under the hot sun. However, the staff do notify the diners regarding the 45-min dining time before they are seated.

In terms of food quality it's definitely there. Slight waiting time for the food, probably due to manpower shortages.

It's a place worth recommending for those who loves Mexican cuisine. Especially for friends & couples, due to the small size of the place.

The food we ordered in the picture;
- Al Pastor Quesadilla
- Baja Fish Taco
- Birria Beef Taco"}

author: Melissa Poh
description:
{'en': 'No complaints just good Mexican food. Fresh ingredients and bright flavours.

Favourites from tonight were the fish tacos, sea bream ceviche, elotes and  loaded nachos. Would definitely recommended for any who loves / is craving for Mexican food :))

Side note for the team:
The paper under the loaded nachos started tearing nearing the end of the dish and some mouthfuls had bits of paper in it! Not sure if others experienced this as well but just some feedback.'}

author: JM
description: {'en': 'Love the Mexican food here. We have revisited 3 times and my favs are the baja fish & chicken quesadilla. Staff are very attentive & efficient. Very popular with long queues whenever I visit on Sat for dinner, so come earlier if you can!'}
owner_responses: {'en': {'text': 'Love u jasmine'}}

author: Rachel Lau
description: {'en': 'One of the best nachos in Singapore, crunchy and with big portion of guacamole, cream cheese, meat & others. Scallop ceviche, cauliflower, the mushrooms side dish were nice too!'}
owner_responses:
{'en': {'text': "Hola Rachel,

Thank you so much for your lovely review!

We‚Äôre glad that you enjoyed dining here.
It warms our heart knowing we are doing something right.
We will strive to continue to do our best in serving you guys!

It's always great to see a familiar face ‚Äî looking forward to welcoming you again at Huevos!

Cheers,
Huevos"}}

author: cjhj
description: {'en': "Rule number 1, don't come during peak hours then complain about waiting time.\nRule number 2, there's unlabeled reaper sauce, try at your own risk.\nRule number 3, when they say the nachos is loaded, it is very very loaded."}

author: XY
description:
{'en': 'The quesadillas and burritos are simply delicious. Had chicken and pork, both were great.

Their homemade chili are amazing. Very hot, but definitely worth the challenge!

The burrito is so huge, very well worth the money. Quesadilla is crispy and yummy.

Super great service by the staff, friendly and thorough with their explanation of the different types of chili available.'}

author: Joanne Guan
description: {'en': 'Saw the great reviews so decided to give this place a go! So glad I tried this place! I‚Äôll add it to my favourites list now! Highly recommend their loaded nachosüòçcome early on the weekends so you avoid the queueüòå'}

author: Paul Brindley
description: {'en': 'Go here. You won‚Äôt be disappointed. Small and cosy with friendly service. Casual atmosphere with really tasty food. Perfect for satisfying that Mexican craving. Loaded nachos, mushroom quesadilla and fish tacos were my top pics.'}

author: Olivia
description: {'en': 'Really great food that won‚Äôt break the bank! The place is pretty small so do expect to queue for a bit, but it‚Äôs worth it.\nThe spiced fish and beef tacos are sooo good!'}

author: Paulo Victor
description: {'en': 'The tacos are fantastic! Make sure you reserve your table bc it is quite a popular place. The fish and beef rib tacos are a must try, definitely coming back to try other menu options. Their homemade carolina reaper sauce is no joke haha loved the staff, very friendly! Price is affordable as well, overall great experience. Super recommend this place!'}
owner_responses:
{'en': {'text': "Hola Paulo!

Thank you for your lovely review!

Warmest Regards,

author: Selvi
description: {'en': 'Worth the queue. Nice food. Nice portion. Parking was full so we went to textile centre. I got recommendation from my bff. She said they have best mexican food. Indeed !!!!'}

author: Raphaela
description: {'en': 'Second time back here because we love the food. So far, everything that we‚Äôve tried has been good. I especially recommend the loaded nachos. Good service from passionate owners.\n\nThe only downside was that we were placed at the bar seat which had very little leg room and counter space. The owner did ask if we were ok with it beforehand but in the future, I would opt for a table instead.'}

author: Jessica Yeo
description: {'en': 'Really good and affordable Mexican food! Loved the burrito bowl - super flavourful and packed with loads of ingredients. Cauli-bites and Baja Tacos are our usual go-to. Service folks were really nice and friendly too!'}

Warmest Regards,

author: Tan Sean
description: {'en': 'Highly recommend the nachos. Fish tacos were generous. The beef tacos were decent too. Customer service is excellent. Quesadillas were okay, not a favourite. come early because queue is crazy'}

author: Zhihua Yu
description: {'en': "Amazing birra! Comparable to the delicious ones I've had in California! Also very accommodating with my young kids, making sure the food wasn't spicy for them. Will Def come back to try the barbacoa!"}

author: RCSC
description: {'en': 'Ordered by OddleEats delivery and OMG sooo blown away by the quality and taste of the foodddd!!! It came hot and still fresh. This is my go to for mexican delivery anytime I am craving for it!'}

author: Brenda Yeong
description:
{'en': "This might be my top restaurant for 2022... and it's only april haha. Definitely the best mexican food I've had in Singapore, far better than Papi's Tacos and Muchachos in terms of both flavour and price.

Ordered the elotes, mushroom quesadilla, chipotle chicken tacos, baja fish tacos and prawn tacos. The chipotle chicken was so flavourful (although there was quite a bit of chicken skin), the baja fish is a truly generous portion of crispy fish, and the prawns were good and crunchy. Loved their salsa and guac, which were fresh and had some kick to them. The hot sauces were also really tangy and tasty. Definitely not for those who cannot take spice though!

Spent about 70 bucks for 3 people, which is pretty affordable imo! Was afraid of the queues after seeing previous reviews, and although the restaurant was small, there were seats on a sunday night between 6-7pm. Also helped that they are super efficient - we were in and out in 45mins.

Will definitely be back to try the beef offerings and to have the chipotle chicken and baja fish again. I'm salivating just thinking about it. Thanks for the great experience!"}

author: Twentyone Purplehorses
description: {'en': 'My brother brought my family here after he ate here a few times and told us it‚Äôs the best Mexican food he‚Äôs had. He‚Äôs not wrong. The staff are kind, food is amazing and we had a wonderful experience here.'}

author: Shaharaj Ahmed
description: {'en': 'Top notch. Highly recommend coming here for a date or with friends. Ordered nachos, beef and fish tacos. The nachos were very generous, beef tacos (birria) were juicy, flavourful, and dripping with sauce. Fish was fresh and tangy. Very friendly staff!'}

author: Unconventional Passionss
Christy L
description: {'en': 'Long queue and unable to book on weekend but it‚Äôs understandable since the food is really 10/10. Compared to the other fast food chain in Singapore, this is truly an authentic ‚Äúmexican experience‚Äù as they promise. Upon opening their menu, you might be confused because of the terms like ‚Äúbirria‚Äù etc etc but look at Google Review images and it can roughly tell you what the dish is. Other than that, the food was portioned quite well and the taste was amazing. I would love to visit it again but this time, with a reservation.'}

author: Joash Quek
description: {'en': 'The burritos and quesadillas are really well done and flavourful. They provide salsa with diff level of hotness. Even the lightest packs a punch so add with caution. Will definitely come back for my Mexican food fix!'}

author: Yan
description: {'en': 'Fish tacos are sooooo good!  Makes me want to go back just by looking at the photo. Love the salsa sauces (level 1-4). If you are craving nachos, I would recommend loaded nachos over nachos with dips since it‚Äôs fairly pricey for just nachos and dips $15++! :)\n\nWill definitely be back for more!'}

author: Chandler Lim
description: {'en': 'amazing food. pretty staff. üëçüèªüëçüèª\nedited: came here again. food still slaps. Quality is consistent. Customer service is great. Staff are friendly and attentive. Pretty staff is still there.'}

author: alexa
description: {'en': 'pretty solid mexican food. got the birria beef tacos and pork quesadillas, both of which were tasty. service was good as well, the waiter was very attentive. the establishment is a bit small so it gets crowded quickly - best to make a reservation.'}

author: Mary Rose Manlangit
description: {'en': "Best Mexican food I've ever tried in SG! Discovered the place on Grab delivery so had to make sure the food is as good when ordered in person. Must try tho expect to line up!"}

author: adam hippo
description: {'en': 'Had dinner here with some friend, very fast service, very nice food. Would recommend to everyone and their moms'}

author: Reuel Ngo
garlic videos
description:
{'en': 'Huevos was absolutely incredible. The food was tantalising on my tastebuds and every mouthful was just an explosion of flavour. I can‚Äôt even begin to describe the things that the burrito wrap I ordered did to my palette, because it was just one massive flavour bomb. Same goes for the Beef Birria Tacos, the consomm√© was the absolute icing on top. They‚Äôre super generous with their portions and every bite was packed full of meat.

They offer up two of their own in-house chilli sauces for use when dining here. One red one green. Both sauces were pretty good but I preferred the green one more. That being said I didn‚Äôt really have the sauces with my food anyways because I find that it drowns out the banging flavour of the food itself.

The atmosphere and decor does not let down either. Although it doesn‚Äôt really pull you into the borders of Mexico, it still gives you the vibe of what you‚Äôre about to be served. And while the store may appear to be on the smaller side at first glance, it makes up for it by having two floors, doubling its seating capacity.

The drinks were pretty special too. We ordered a slushie and some rice drink, and they both had fantastic flavours.

Definitely gonna come here again cause oh my god the food is so good.'}

author: Bryan Loo
description: {'en': 'Second time having Huevos, this time getting it delivered via Oddle. We got the prawn, chicken, and beef birria tacos, the chicken and pork quesadillas, and the elotes.\n\n10/10 would recommend. Food was great even after being delivered!!'}
owner_responses:
{'en': {'text': 'Hola Bryan!

Thank you for your bussin kind review.
It makes our day like nothing else <3
11/10 hope to welcome you again

<3
Huevos'}}

description: {'en': 'Great value for the food. Food is great and staff very helpful. They even have their homemade jalapeno pepper mix.\n\nSeats are quite limited though.'}

It's always great to see a familiar face ‚Äî looking forward to welcoming you again at Huevos!

Huevos"}}

author: cecilia zhuang
description: {'en': 'The food here is amazing! Satisfied my craving for Mexican food. Will definitely come back for more.'}

author: Betrice Yambrach
description: {'en': 'Amazing. I can‚Äôt wait to go back. Holy hell this place was good. Either make a reservation for a weekday, or show up before 5pm on the weekend for a spot. Will be worth the wait.'}

author: Min Htun Zaw
description: {'en': 'Recomended by my daughter and tried it. Really authentic mexican food. I saw every table ordered Nachos and we did which was right choice. Tacos were nice too.'}

author: Haoye Fu
